2.description: This forum is for website based updates on the forum, as well as any server-based improvements.

7.name: Hack Request
7.description: Want us to create a trainer / hack for a game? Why not request it here, we like a challenge, doesn't have to be a rhythm game (please be realistic).

9.name: osu! Cheat Discussion
9.description: Discuss cheating in osu! and the use of The Aquila Network's programs in such a game, discuss and share .CT cheat engine tables if you have any good ones :3.

10.name: osu! General Chat
10.description: Talk about anything and everything here.

11.name: osu! Showoff Section
11.description: Post some extraordinary plays with our cheats or without on osu! here (but please don't spam with every single one of your #1s, go for amazing shit like DT Chipscape or something). Also we don't care if you are like "holy balls, I just beat White Wolf in a song".

13.name: Dashie's Sky Racing
13.description: An upcoming XNA game being coded by Annie the Eagle, on his own in C#.

14.name: FPS / Shooter Games
14.description: Talk about games like Battlefield 3, Call of Duty, Hard Reset and Crysis.

15.name: RPG / MMORPG Games
15.description: Discuss adventure games like The Elder Scrolls series (Oblivion, Skyrim), World of Warcraft.

16.name: Action Games
16.description: Talk about any good action games like Just Cause, Mass Effect 3, Assassin's Creed Series.

17.name: Sandbox Games
17.description: Have some fun talking about the creativity you can get from Sandbox games like Garry's Mod and LittleBigPlanet (Note: Sandbox Games are those where you can create levels and/or edit levels, just look at LittleBigPlanet or Garry's Mod for an idea)

18.name: Other Games

19.name: Off Topic
19.description: Just for the registered members, feel free to discuss things going on in life, sports, hobbies, etc.

1.subject: The Aquila Network is BACK
1.message:
[size=large][b]The Aquila Network is BACK![/b]

Well it was a rollercoaster of failure but we are now finally back and should be once and for all!

Expect much more content now and thanks for your patience guys! <3
[/size]

3.subject: RE: The Aquila Network is BACK
3.message: Awesome, I was away for the weekend.  This was a really nice surprise to find tonight :)

4.subject: Kev
4.message:
Well Annie and I are coding partners, we met thanks to geckogates a while back (Thanks for allowing us to collaborate together if you read this.)  

I'm nothing special, learned how to program in C++ thanks to creating osu! hacks and bots.  I feel as though I have my own unique methods to tearing apart the game, and I find fun in having unfair advantages over other players.  I really enjoy watching idiots get pissed off over the things I do, please don't be one of these people if you sign up on the site.

About myself:  I like to program when I get free time, I often bot/play WoW, I will be playing D3 when it comes out also.  I'd say I love to find bugs/exploits in things, as well as think of a method on how it could easily be avoided. 
I like to listen to Metal/Rock/Techno/Trance music the most, I really don't like most of the Anime songs in osu!  :(.

15.subject: RE: TimeWarp
15.message:
The TimeWarp actually works through a method other then that of which Cheat Engine does.  Cheat Engine speeds up the whole process, TimeWarp only speeds up part of the program and adjusts memory values so that the score submits.  It was found entirely by mistake when I was bored, Annie and I have capitalized on what it can do and I still have a few plans for it.

I don't want to release the method as to how it works, so I left it generalized.  I hope you understand.

This hack is not new but I want to tell you about it.  (Kev Edit: This is Hanyu's hack by the way...)

[align=center]Video of how it works.

[size=xx-small]Idea by [url=http://osufuture.blogspot.com/]Hanyu[/url].[/size][/align]


[size=large][b]Some requirements if you want to use it:[/b][/size]

1. It's only stealth for current osu! version.
2. You have to understand where this will lead.
3. You have been warned. :exclamation:
4. The map will be credited with a flashlight on only the first try.
After that, you need to reconnect with osu! to hack is work again. Otherwise, the maps you're playing with a flashlight or not will not be counted ranked.

[b][size=large]Instruction:[/size][/b]
[list=1]

272.subject: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
272.message:
[b]Changeset #41[/b]

[b]Release Type:[/b] No release.
[b]Build Type:[/b] Alpha.

[b][u]Comments[/u][/b]
Woo, I got my first powerup working correctly, Autopilot, while currently can be triggered on demand by pressing A, soon it will be made so that when generating the random race, it will also create powerups (between 1 and 3  0 - 1 on Heroic, 0 on Extreme) and they will be placed in easy to see but generally pain in the ass places but will give a good reward if collected.

[Autopilot] - Increases players speed to the maximum speed of the pony and flies automatically for 3 seconds (1.5 seconds on Heroic).

I have also added between 5 and 6 moveable rings per race that will move the full range of Y values and also fixed both players autopilots to handle it correctly.

Next changeset I want to add the actual powerups and remove the on-demand key, as well as add Heroic modifications.


[b][u]Changelog[/u][/b]
+ [Gameplay] Added moveable rings that will move through the whole range of Y values (for normal races).
+ [Gameplay] Added random generation of moveable rings so will always be different every race (5 or 6 per race).
+ [Gameplay] Completed the Autopilot powerup for players that will steer for them and fly at full speed for 3 seconds (1 on Heroic).
* [Code] Fixed the name of NormalRaceScreen (it only had one e  DERP).
* [Database] Adjusted opponent speeds to the new movement speed leniency.
* [Gameplay] Made the movement speeds much more lenient to make the same speed require less key press speed. Doesnt kill your hands anymore :3
* [Gameplay] Fixed the opponents autopilot to correctly handle the moving rings now (it will update every frame if the current ring index for the opponent is found within the moveableRings array).
* [Gameplay] Fixed the finishing ring to no longer be within the range of random values for the moveablerings.
* [Gameplay] Fixed the countdown not resuming if the Resume option was pressed instead of using ESC.
@ Version 0.23 Update 1 (Alpha)

390.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
390.message:
[b]Changeset #43 (Alpha)[/b]

[b][u]Comments[/u][/b]
Ive been a derp, I used the incorrect name for a pony because I mistakenly read the description of a vector on DeviantART rather than the title (which contained the correct name), total DERP!

Anyway, other than fixing that and some other stuff that I had wanted to fix for a while, Ive added another pony to race against. Flitter, and raised the maximum level to 60.

[u][b]Changeset Details[/b][/u]

+ [Database] Added another pony Flitter.
+ [Graphics] Added flitters sprite and character pane sprite into the database.
* [Database] Corrected Rainy Days name, changed to Lightning Bolt. (Silly DeviantART).
* [Graphics] Corrected Lightning Bolts Sprite Name.
* [Graphics] Fixed the origin of a few characters
* [Graphics] Fixed the size of the character pane images being about 4 pixels to large.
* [Graphics] Fixed the huge size of Flitters Sprite.
* [Progression] Corrected the massive XP gains from Speedy Win Bonus.
* [Progression] Changed the amount of levels needed to get to certain characters.
* [Progression] Increased the maximum level to 60.
@ Version 0.23 Update 3 (Alpha)

[quote='Kev' pid='403' dateline='1335731304']
He's been working on this for about a month now it seems, I've yet to actually play the game on my computer, but I've seen it on his.  Doesn't look to bad for a solo developed project.
[/quote]

Yeah, while I understand the things you said in the Skype Call that the sprites are static and need to be animated, understand that I am no good at animation in the slightest and I am basically using *borrowed* vectors from MLP-VectorClub from DeviantART. Also, I am currently focusing more on gameplay and then refining graphics. Look at osu! when it first started, it wasn't looking very good. I added Parallax scrolling a while ago though so that'll be nice to see =). 422.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
422.message:
[u][b]Changeset #44[/b][/u]

[b][u]Comments[/u][/b]
I know I said that I wasnt gonna post any changes today but apparently I forgot to commit this update yesterday so Ill just go ahead and commit it today, although I did add 3 more graphics into it because I was playing around with Photoshop :3

[u]Changeset Details[/u]
+ [Graphics] Added the ??? Pony that is shown in the character pane if there is no user profile found.
+ [Graphics] Added the storm cloud and progression indicator that will be used later for features (probably will add progression indicator tommorow).
* [Code] Moved the loading of character pane info from MainMenuScreen to MenuScreen, allows for much more efficent checks.
* [Code] Fixed variable shadowing on GameModeSelectScreen
* [Error Handling] Now properly handles file errors during XP updates, will now catch exceptions such as File in use or File non existant.
* [Graphics] Fixed the character pane sprite not changing on a Reset Player Profile option.
@ Version 0.23 Update 4 (Alpha)

470.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
470.message:
[b][u]Changeset #45 (Alpha)[/u][/b]

[b][u]Comments[/u][/b]
Well I said I'd have the progression indicator done soon, and yes I have just gosh darn done that, it was quite fiddly to get the positions right but now it's done :3 and I also added a function that I wanted to add for a while that was to get the difference required between two levels on command. I also added the progression indicator percentage and fixed that around a little and improved the visual aesthetics of the race screens "HUD" slightly.

All in all, quite pleased with this changeset :D

[b][u]Changeset Details[/u][/b]
+ [Code] Added a function in Game_Functions.Experience to calculate the experience required between ANY two levels.#
+ [Gameplay] Added a progression display that will show on the RaceCompleteScreen and display the actual percentage between unlocking characters.
+ [Fonts] Added a new font for the ranks during the gameplay.
* [Fonts] Changed the size of the timer in the top left corner of the race.
* [Fonts] Changed the font used to draw the text in the speed bar.
* [Gameplay] Fixed the sprite of the progression indicator to be slightly wider and allow for a "%" symbol.
* [Graphics] Fixed the player userarea sprite not changing to "???" Pony on a reset player profile option.
* [Graphics] Improved the fonts that the rank display uses, increased the clarity of ranks and changed the rankBG design.
* [Graphics] Improved the drawing of the rank display and added a less blurry font. 
@ Version 0.24 Update 1 (Alpha).

473.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
473.message:
[b][u]Changeset #46 (Alpha)[/u][/b]

[b][u]Developer Notes[/u][/b]
I got quite carried away with this changeset, more ideas just kept popping up as I was doing it, it was a great PRODUCTIVE trance that allowed me to refine some more rubbish that I had left behind as well as add some more eye-pleasing visuals.

I wont make a huge post about my thoughts on this one as the changeset details speak for themselves, but just as a sort of teaser for whats coming in Changeset #47 and #48.

#47 will be a graphics uphaul, one of the problems I have discovered with XNAs SpriteDrawing is that even with PreferMultisampling = true;, it still blows when it comes to drawing sprites err round about anywhere less than 0.40 (in either direction or BOTH). Photoshop however, DOES have many resampling algorithms that make it look smooth and non-jagged, so the next changeset will be finding sprites that are always drawn at a size less than 1.00, and change them in Photoshop to the correct size, then increasing the scale in the game to 1.00, thus making them sharper and nicer.

#48 is the big one, Im going to try and add a new race, and background scrolling clouds and maybe a background scrolling image, as the game currently runs at 1280 x 720, the background may be 1920 x 720, this allows scrolling smoothly during the race and makes things actually appear MOVING!

Thats all for now :3 (The post turned out longer than I wanted :{)

[b][u]Changeset Details[/u][/b]
+ [Code] Added function to calculate player index just by supplying the players level.
+ [Graphics] Added a new speed bar in the shape of a lightning bolt and matching fill. Will also create a new specials bar.
+ [Graphics] Added a level 100 trophy sprite in the progression when the player is on the highest pony.
* [Code] Changed the Reset and No Profile to Reference sprite 9 rather than 8 (as 8 is the Level 100 Trophy).
* [Database] Increased the maximum playersprites to 9 (to add the Level 100 Trophy).
* [Error Handing] Fixed the XP being written to file in scientific notation such as 1.7E+007 which would crash the reading as scientific notation when called .ToString results in NULL.
* [Gameplay] Increased the length of races the harder (and faster) the opponent. (Up to 37,000 at Princess Celestia).
* [Gameplay] Increased the randomness of each ring from 55 to 100 each side.
* [Gameplay] Increased the threshold to charge the Rainboom bar to 14.00 rather than 13.60 to work better with the more lenient player speed introduced a few changesets back.
* [Gameplay] Reduced the max-speed of rainboom charge by 75% (0.40f to 0.10f).
* [Gameplay] Changed it so that the rainboom will now remove all speed reductions from ringmisses upon activation
* [Gameplay] Autopilot will not longer be collected if rainboom is active.
* [Gameplay] Autopilot will now charge the rainboom at 50% of the maximum rate.
* [Gameplay] Removed the discharging of the rainboom bar if the players speed is not high enough.
* [Gameplay] Increased the duration of RAINBOOM by 50%.
* [Gameplay] Reworked Distance XP gains to stack better with leveling.
* [Gameplay] Raised the determination if the player has passed the ring to 3 more pixels either side, as sometimes in Rainbow Dashs Rainboom Special, it would miss the determination completely.
* [Graphics] Fixed the INSANE size of the Level 100 Trophy Sprite (forgot to downsize it by 90% on Photoshop, DERPY).
* [Graphics] Tweaked the positioning of the progression indicator text slightly.
* [Graphics] Changed the way the lightningspeedfill is drawn, rather than using width, it will use the SourceRectangle.
* [Wording] Reworded the Race Win XP to Race Completion XP.
@ Version 0.24 Update 7 (Alpha).

I haven't forgotten about this project, oh no no, one does not simply forget about Rainbow Dash games. 634.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
634.message:
[b]Changeset #51 (Alpha)[/b]

[b][u]Developer Comments[/u][/b]
Yes! I finally managed to finish the Freeplay mode, and while it currently only allows you to change the ponies you are racing as and against, it will eventually also allow you to tweak race settings like ring size, ring difficulty (harshness of the turns), powerup spawn frequency and overall difficulty.

I have also managed to create more MOUSE interaction, which is where I want to go with this eventually by adding RACE! buttons and stuff!

Hopefully tomorrow I can work on improving the opponent's autopilot logic so that it uses virtual "keys", and this will then eventually be used for the Autoplay mode (where you can watch how the computer would play a race).

[b][u]Changeset Details[/u][/b]
+ [Code] Added a button entry class that can be used to create buttons freely, handling input currently on a per-screen basis.
+ [Code] Added logic handling during race screen for Freeplay modes.
+ [Database] Added freeplay level requirements to unlock the ponies, this is currently set to 1 stage BELOW campaign (i.e. "Spitfire the Wonderbolt" requires level 20 in Freeplay but Level 30 in Campaign).
+ [Fonts] Added another font for the Level Requirement Lock if the character in freeplay is not available.
+ [Gameplay] Continued work on the characterEntry to now make it selectable and expand when selected.
+ [Gameplay] Added FreeplayScreen where a player can create a custom race for themselves and the CPU.
+ [Gameplay] Added a constructor for NormalRaceScreen which can handle freeplay races AND campaign races.
+ [Gameplay] Added a race progress indicator that is shown during the race to show how far the player and opponent is.
+ [Graphics] Added the Princess Celestia Character Pane Sprite
+ [Graphics] Added cursor scaling when clicking, this will also unhide the cursor.
+ [Graphics] Added a Princess Celestia image that you is used for Freeplay.
+ [Graphics] Added a padlock image for locked characters in freeplay mode.
* [Code] Fixed PauseScreen handling of both Freeplay and Campaign races, this will now work correctly and remember your current race settings.
* [Code] Fixed the ClickOnce crap that I don't want to use anymore, removed all the depencies and fixed the project settings.
* [Code] Fixed the "Somepony" character sprite reference from [9] to [10].
* [Database] Increased Fluttershy's opponent speed from 0 to 8.80, this is for the Freeplay Mode, as in campaign, the opponent NEVER uses Fluttershy.
* [Graphics] Fixed the position of the usage text in the messagebox pop up.
- [Code] Removed the final reference to loading XNA's Terrible GamerServices module.
@ Version 0.26 Update 1 (Alpha)

659.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
659.message:
[b]Changeset #52 (Alpha)[/b]

[u][b]Developer Comments[/b][/u]
I haven't made any updates on this blog for 6 days as I've been deciding with the help of my TI-Nspire CAS's graphic functions and Excel on how to rework the Experience System, it was pretty fiddly in getting it balanced so that the early levels didn't go ultra fast and the high levels went super slow! I hope to have finally fixed this at least with a much better system.

I also added a ingame score display that will tie in with this new system as the current XP system is completely scrapped, it has been replaced with "Total Score", which allows it to stack much better and make the calculation functions a lot less complex and more simple but effective.

The final thing was a bunch of bugfixes that have been "bugging" (no pun intended) me for a while. That's all done now and the next stage is to get the Accuracy Display working and make it more tidier as well as some other things that I'll keep secret for now :3


[b][u]Changeset Details[/u][/b]
+ [Code] [Gameplay] [Progression] Reworked the experience system and has now been renamed to "Total Score", this will work hand in hand with the planned online ranking scoreboards.
+ [Code] Added a new class "Score.cs" to handle the race's score metrics such as Accuracy, Rings Hit / Missed, Score and Combo Display.
+ [Fonts] Added a font for the Score and Accuracy display in game.
+ [Gameplay] Added a display of score and accuracy during the race. This is now backend-supported with the reworked experience system.
+ [Gameplay] Added a better way of calculating accuracy rather than relying on in-built variables, it uses the new class variables.
* [Code] [Progression] Completely reworked the Score Gains system during each race. Totally reworked it to make it more friendly to the new system.
* [Code] [Progression] [Gameplay] Redesigned the handling and display of Score Gains at the end of each race, saving much more efficent and the calculation of the "NEXT UNLOCK" feature is much faster.
* [Code] Minor refactors and performance enchancements on FreeplayModeScreen.cs
* [Database] Adjusted unlocking of pony level requirements.
* [Fonts] Renamed the XPFont to a raceCompleteFont as that is the only place it is used.
* [Gameplay] Fixed the rainboom meter charging during autopilot if the player's pony was NOT Rainbow Dash.
* [Gameplay] Increased the length of the Autopilot pickup by 1 second (now 4 seconds, up from 3).
* [Global] Changed all references and content references of XP to Score, in lieu of the new system.
* [Graphics] Remodeled the User Pane Area in the bottom left hand side to be more sleek and have the level shown to the right of the Score Bar. Will soon add overall accuracy display.
* [Player Save] Reworked the structure of the file to be more explanatory (for now).
@ Version 0.26 Update 3

660.subject: RE: Dashie's Sky Racing - Changelog
660.message:
Changeset ID: #53
Release Type: No Release
Build Type: Alpha ()

I wanted to finish the metrics today so I did so and fixed some other bugs that I wanted to fix, the next thing I want to work on now is more ponies and add the difficulty settings to actually have an effect on the gameplay.
I also want to start PLANNING a new game-mode that is unlocked at Level 60, which is called Endurance Mode, where you are racing for as long as you possibly can, its an infinite map that generates as you go and will allow you to play and get huge Score Gains to level up and unlock ponies faster, and you can also compete (when available) online on the Endurance Leaderboards (one for each game difficulty).

Changeset Details
+ [Gameplay] Added total races played and accuracy metrics to the user pane.
+ [Player Save] Added the new metrics to the savefile.
+ [Progression] Added calculation functions in Progression.cs and RacingCompleteScreen.cs
* [Graphics] Fixed the position of some of the Score Gain Values in the RacingCompleteScreen
* [Graphics] Fixed the level string if there is no profile.
* [Player Save] When erasing your profile via the options, all values are now correctly reset.
@ Version 0.27 Update 1 (Alpha)

882.subject: osu!Relax v5.02 Download and Change Log
882.message:
[img]http://i.imgur.com/8ifzJus.png[/img]
GUI design thanks to: [url=http://www.theaquila.net/member.php?action=profile&uid=1551]TehTalii[/url] and me :P

[b]Download:[/b]
(Please note that this is packed with Themida, it is known to set off false positives to Anti-Viruses.)
[url=http://www.theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Relax/osu!Relax v5.02.rar]osu!Relax v5.02[/url]

For those with a missing .dll (place this next to the bot):  http://puu.sh/22zAs

[b]Things to add:[/b]
Perhaps a more detailed GUI with the hotkeys and such to press, and a config editing GUI.

[b]Things to fix:[/b]

[b]Change Logs:[/b]
[spoiler]
[b]Fixes/additions and released in v5.02 (Oct 30th.):[/b]
Quick update to fix some issues that users are having with not reading the song timer.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v5.01 (Oct 4th.):[/b]
Quick update to fix relax detecting spectator when playing.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v5.00 (Aug 26th.):[/b]
Fixed an issue with songs containing ">".
Fixed the DT in multiplayer issue.
Restarting a song now will give new note offsets.
Console GUI.
New config GUI, no more opening in notepad to edit.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.25 (Aug 1st.):[/b]
Just updating with the recent osu! update to maintain functionality with TimeWarp.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.23 (June 11th.):[/b]
Fixed an issue with Disabling Bancho (via TimeWarp) where the bot would think the song had ended.
Fixed an issue where restarting the song would cause timing issues in the beginning of the song.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.22 (June 10th.):[/b]
Fixed a bug where first login would be likely to have the bot thinking Hard Rock was enabled.
Fixed an issue with some file version detections.
Fixed some issues where the random offsetting function would cause different streaming patterns.  

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.21 (June 3rd.):[/b]
Removed a cout left in there for debugging.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.20 (June 3rd.):[/b]
New offset note system.  It is highly advised to not tweak the new config variable by much!
New login system on the bot, complete with a GUI, it now supports symbols in the password and spaces in the username.
New main GUI.
More customization on spinner behavior allowing the user to manually press keys for spinning if they wish.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.02 (Mar 6th.):[/b]
Fixed key alternation issues.
Added TimeWarp communication.
Removed useless data being displayed.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.01 (Feb 28th.):[/b]
Fixed a bug where if the GUI wasn't showing and Hard Rock was toggled, it wouldn't work.
Added support for v12 osu file format.  (Should fix issues with playing the newest maps.)

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v4.00 (Feb 28th.):[/b]
Added a mini GUI. (This can be disabled.)
Allowed hiding of console window.
Fixed sending keypress after exiting song.
Fixed an issue regarding Nightcore speed songs.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v3.02 (Feb 21st.):[/b]
Fixed StreamTime not scaling to song time.
Changed how the song quit detection works.
Detects reset song.
Added delay keys for in-game play.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v3.01 (Feb 13th.):[/b]
Fixed sliders/spinners not accounting for song speed.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v3.00 (Feb 13th.):[/b]
Note Detection added, will now detect where the mouse cursor is.
Hotkeys in game play temporarily removed, will be added very soon.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.72:[/b]
Downloading issue has been fixed, I'm positive it has been.
Found and fixed another issue that would make the bot release a slider early.
Reading the song timer has become so precise, I advise using ClickOffset 0.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.71:[/b]
Should have fixed the bug that caused Relax to let go of sliders early.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.70:[/b]
Better CUI (Thanks Annie :3)
Saving logins, no more retyping!

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.66:[/b]
Fixed slider issues regarding v10 and v11 files.
Calculated for random offsets causing sliders to let go early.
/\ (will happen once in a while though.)
Fixed RandomOffsets 0 crash bug.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.65:[/b]
V10 and V11 file support added.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.64:[/b]
Random offsets wasn't working properly, fixed it (should really decrease detection rates now.)
Minor changes.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.63:[/b]
Two new key patterns!
Definable stream time also.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.60:[/b]
Pausing is supported again.
Detects spectator mode and enters Idle Mode.
Detects speed of song.
Faster start up.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.50:[/b]
No more memory pointers!  (Perhaps Peppy will have a harder time patching.)
No need to select the osu! window, auto detecting now.
Still have to play start to finish.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.40:[/b]
Updated for the new song timing method.
Changed how configs work.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.35:[/b]
Randomization config option added.  Users should add this to their configs, it will greatly help when a user places a 1st place ranking, you should have less chance in bans.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.34:[/b]
Win XP supported, finally works fine.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.33:[/b]
Reversed the way ALT works.
Minor features added.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.31:[/b]
Spectate key added, this is Idle Mode.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.30:[/b]
Added an updating system.
Detects when the song list is not parsed.
Daily Messages are now displayed.  This would be my way of contacting users who are lazy :3.
Fixed a bug that would might cause keys to continue being held down after moving from the pause to the menu.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.23:[/b]
Added a new offset system, hold down right ALT while playing and it will gradually offset your hits.
Fixed a text display issue.
Awaiting song or key command is now five times faster to respond.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.22:[/b]
Windows XP supported now.  Took forever to do this.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.21:[/b]
Found a slider that it missed at the end, proceeded to fix missing sliders as last note.  (It's late.)

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.20:[/b]
User is now able to specify what percentage they would like to aim for in a song.  It is advised to keep it above 90%.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.14:[/b]
Last note issues fixed, this was caused only after playing the first song.
Found a bug where the program would reload the song list by itself, but did not load it into memory.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v2.13:[/b]
Custom user key pressings. Only working for a-z and 0-9.
Reload config when edited.
Also fixed an issue with the login system.
Added a message for the space key to hit 100s.  (This was a feature since the first release, don't know why I mentioned it.)

[b]Fixed and released in v2.12:[/b]
Miss grabbing in multi time to time. 

[b]Fixed and released in v2.11:[/b]
Crashes on start of some songs.
Detecting song back at menu 
Not hitting last note on certain songs 
[/spoiler]

I will continue to update this as needed.

904.subject: Few things I've noticed
904.message:
I've been using it for about 3~4 hours of playtime, and so far it is working very well and above expectations!

Here's a few minor quirks I've noticed:
In a multiplayer match, the last hitobject was a spinner and it would 'click' for me for a second and let go, well before the spinner ended. (Just 1 match though, haven't tried to replicate it yet)

In solo, the program would read "Finished" when you fail during play.
If you click retry, it won't print "Reset", instead it would act as if you returned to the song selection menu. (Probably not a bug, more like a small design flaw)


Here are a few suggestions for new features (Take them with a grain of salt because I don't know how feasible these would be to code them):

If you've tried the Relax mod implemented in osu! itself, you would have noticed that it not only clicks for you, but it 'compensates', as in :
If you move your cursor over a hitobject later than the '300 timing window', it would click anyway, giving you a 100 or a 50.
This feature, if implemented, would probably help out people who are trying to play/full combo difficult maps with this program.
(Though you'd have to write code to detect the position of the cursor and so on :-/)
We don't need the widened timing window or the faster RPM in a spinner handicaps that the osu! relax gives IMO, it'd be easily noticeable.

905.subject: RE: Few things I've noticed
905.message:
I had that first issue you were talking about, but I haven't had it happened again.

The failing the song will treat it much like you went back to menu, there will be about a 6 second delay before it loads the song back up.  But there is also a bug with the multiplayer window grabbing if you have to wait for a user to start their song.  I fixed that, but haven't released it yet.  


About your suggestion:

It would be nearly impossible with the way I programmed it.  I made it so that it does not even bother with the note location.  I have not perfected locating the notes, even my osu!bot that I have been programming and restarting that project multiple times, has not once been perfect on the mouse positions.  I sadly don't have plans to add that feature in :(.  I used a bot like this for a month and did pretty well once I got used to it.

I'll put up an updated hopefully at the end of tonight with custom key abilities.  (a-z and 0-9 only.)

906.message:

In other words, would it be possible to set a 'frequency' value so that when the bot clicks, it would click with the set maximum ClickOffset value with less/more frequency depending on what the user set the 'frequency' value as.
One way to do this would be to set the 'frequency' value to be a percentage, so that each time a bot clicks, it would click with the set maximum ClickOffset value with a x% chance.

974.subject: Ghost recorder!!!
974.message:
Introduction
Ghost recorder was written by me

Note that this is a WIP!

Feel free to ask questions. pm me

How to build Ghost recorder
I do not provide binaries, as this was by choice. Rather, we provide the necessary source files to compile it yourself. You will need this http://www.microsoft.com/visualstudio/en-us/products/2010-editions/visual-cpp-express  probably to build it. Note that you only need C++; during the installation, it may have an option for SQL Server or something, those are NOT required. Make two separate Win32 Console Applications (Visual C++ >> Win32 >> Win32 Console Application. Make sure you pick console application, not windows application), one for recording and another for playback. Check empty project at the wizard. Now, you'll need to download the actual source of Ghost Recorder. Download a subversion client, the most popular being something like tortoise svn  http://tortoisesvn.net/downloads.html . Create a new folder, in which you will download the project files. If you have install tortoise correctly, you should right click and see the option svn checkout. In there, paste the line from the textfiles  http://puu.sh/EMWg , and hit ok. All the files should now be downloaded. In C++ Express, hit view and then solution explorer. In the "Source Files" folder, add stdafx.cpp to both of the projects. In the playback project, put pla.cpp in the source files, and the recorder put rec.cpp. In both of them, add to the "Header Files" targetver.h and stdafx.h.

How to use Ghost recorder
Getting started
The first part of using osu-ac involves configuring it to use the correct memory addresses. This is done primarily with Cheat Engine http://cheatengine.org/  . Download that, and install it. For the rest of the tutorial, just leave osu! open and attach Cheat Engine to osu!.exe. Note that everytime you restart osu!, you may have to rescan these values (the audio offset and mouse buttons are static, but the mouse pointer can change).

edit: having to re-find the addresses could be remedied by disabling ASLR (address space layout randomization)

Required memory addresses
The recorder uses 4 values to work -

The pointer to the mouse
The right mouse button pressed boolean (rmb)
The left mouse button pressed boolean (lmb)
Byte position (or millisecond) of the audio
Each of these values can be found using the same method in different places. The method to do this easily is to do an initial scan for unknown variable, then use increased/decreased value depending on what you do in the game. Addresses placed in two separate text files - address.txt and address2.txt are in format 0xFFFFFF - 32bit hexadecimal (more on this later).

The text files
osu-ac uses two text files for reading settings

address.txt for recording
address2.txt for playback
Please make sure you make these in the same directory as the executables.

Format for address.txt
Each number represents the line number which the address should be on.

Audio address
Base cursor address
Right mouse button address
Left mouse button address
Example :

0x0031555C
0x03A239D0
0x003153F0
0x00315398
Format for address2.txt
Each number represents the line number which the address should be on.

Audio address
key #1 (the first key you use in osu instead of presses)
key #2 (the second key you use in osu instead of presses)
Example :

0x0031555C
z
x
Addresses of Right Mouse Button/Left Mouse Button
IMPORTANT - YOU MUST DO THIS SEPARATELY FOR EACH INDIVIDUAL BUTTON

Make a replay (make a map with 30sec or whatever of play) where you just click (doesn't matter whether you click or use keyboard), hold for a bit, and release (recommended 10 second intervals between each). Remember to use one button only! A button is represented by a boolean, which has two states. The value of the boolean changes depending on whether it is pressed down or not. When the button is not pressed, it is a 0 and when it is pressed it is 1. Watch the replay, and first scan with "Unknown initial value" in CE. If the button was not held down and then became held down (i.e, when the cursor expands) scan for "increased by 1". Otherwise, if the button was held down and then released, scan for "decreased by 1." Repeat this a few times until you see some values that match up to the pressing/releasing of each button (you don't want the value that relates to EITHER button being pressed). The memory addresses of these go in address.txt on 3rd/4th line, and are constant so don't need to be changed. Now, make sure to do this for the other button as well.

Audio Offset Addresses
Do the same thing as above, except do it while playing the map yourself. Pause the song and search for unknown, then play for a few seconds and search for increased value. Repeat this a few times, then quit out and play again and search for decreased value. It should give you a value that increased quickly (not in milliseconds) as you're playing and relates to the music position (it's the number of bytes processed). So go to main menu and scroll the song with the scroll bar and it should go up/down relative to your changes. Address for this is also constant so doesn't have to be changed. Place it in the 1st line of address.txt. This is also the first line of address2.txt.

Mouse Position Address
The last thing to find changes every run (there is a static version of it, if anyone could tell us how to find it, would be greatly appreciated). Make a replay where you begin with your cursor at the top of the screen, then drag it slowly down to the bottom, and slowly back up to the top. Watch the replay. Scan for unknown at the beginning, and then when the cursor is moving down means your cursor's y value increased, so scan for increased value when it is, and when it's moving up it means the y value decreased, so scan for decreased value. Look for a value that corresponds to the Y (vertical) position of the mouse, as there will be many (note that when your cursor is at about the top it should be close to zero, and when the cursor is near the bottom, it should be close to the height of the window). Once you see this, don't change song or the address will change. Click the value and move it to the bottom with the red arrow, then right click and "find what writes to this address". Agree to attach debugger. You should then see a command being executed "movsd", right click and show in disassembler. a few lines above, there will be a line such as mov edi,03xxxxD0 - the value inside the square brackets is your pointer, should start with 03 and end with D0 (Does not have to). This goes as the 2nd address in address.txt. This value resets each time you run the game, but only takes 20 seconds to find so we didn't bother finding a constant pointer to it.

Using the actual programs
Press F6 in both projects to build them, and put both exes in the same directory, along with address.txt and address2.txt. With all these values in place, you need a folder "replays" inside the same directory as the exes, and then it is almost all automated. Keys Q W E and R change the playback speed, but display the change in console so you can figure it out. With recorder open, any time you enter a song it will automatically record the replay to replays folder. with playback open, it will automatically find a matching replay to use (if it doesn't exist it just does nothing). Press P to stop the current playback (it will also stop if the title changes to osu!).

Additional Notes
Note that the sampling rate during recording is about every 2 ms, so you probably need a decent PC for this to work, otherwise recording/playback will NOT work very well. Note also that not a perfect reproduction of the replay is made, as there can be offsets due to the audio pointer not updating quickly enough. Saved replays should be compatible across machines that use the same osu! resolution.

All in all, do not expect this to be a foolproof method to copy replays - there will be instances where it will fail due to lag during recording or during playback, or a slow updating audio pointer. Secondly, the cursor offset (actual coordinates added in playback) are slightly off, in the future this may need to be fine tuned.

1080.subject: Song Timer Memory Pointer Tutorial - With Video
1080.message:
So I know a few users have had problems with this after updating so I will be doing a step by step guide on how to create a memory pointer for use with osu!Relax, this works with osu!Taiko also!!

[url=http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XmcRmzx6LbY][u][b]Video is here![/b][/u][/url]
[b]You will need:[/b]
osu!
Cheat Engine
Fully Functioning Brain

[b]Step 1:[/b] Load up Cheat Engine and osu!.exe, attach Cheat Engine to osu!.exe

Step 2: At the main menu in osu!, stop the music with the stop button and hit play.  It should start the song from the start, ensure you have a song that is at least a minute long playing.

Step 3: On Cheat Engine change the Scan Type to: "Unknown initial value."  Then click First Scan.
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%203.png[/img]

Step 4: Now while the song is playing, set the scan type to "Increased value" and keep clicking "Next Scan."  

Step 5: After you get down to less than 500 results pause the music in osu!, go back to Cheat Engine and click "Next Scan" once, then change the Scan Type to: "Unchanged value" and click "Next Scan" ONCE.
If done right you will see 5 values that are in milliseconds, the middle one is the most reliable value.  Double click that value in the found address list.
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%205.png[/img]

Step 6:  Now in the bottom box of Cheat Engine where the address has now appeared.  Right click the address and select: "Pointer scan for this address."  Using settings like this (Max Level MUST BE 5!):
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%206.png[/img]

Let this run until finished, and remember where you saved your scan file!

Step 7: I canceled mine early, but it will look something like this when finished scanning:
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%207.png[/img]

Step 8: Restart your computer then load up osu!.exe again.  (This jumbles around the memory pointers.)  Now repeat Steps 1-5

Step 9: After having the address in your list, click the "Memory View" button, on the Memory Viewer go to Tools>Pointer Scan. Now go File>Open and located that pointer scan file you saved back in Step 6. 
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%209.png[/img]

After having loaded the file, click "Pointer scanner>Rescan memory."  Put in the current address of the song timer.
[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%209-2.png[/img]

Hit OK and wait.

Step 10:  You may have to repeat Step 8 and 9 once or twice more, but I highly doubt it.  You have a pointer scan that should work with osu!Relax.  

With that Pointer scan window open, load up the osu!Relax config. (Located in the Data>Configs folder.)

And do something similar to this:

[img]https://dl.dropbox.com/u/17175104/osu%21Relax%20Releases/PtTut/Step%2010.png[/img]


Hopefully this will clear things up for people, I really don't like doing this for people because most of the time they get side tracked and such.  It's an easy task.

1099.subject: How to not get banned after the first ban.
1099.message:
This guide is simply to explain how a user can become "invisible" once more after having multiple banned accounts.

[b]Things you will need:[/b]
[list]
[*][url=http://www.revouninstaller.com/]Revo Uninstaller [/url]
[*][url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=200]A method to change IP addresses[/url]
[*][url=http://puu.sh/GT3F]SMAC  (Download a Torrented crack.)[/url]
[/list]


Step 1:  Back up your song folder, and your skin folder, you do not want to lose these when you use Revo Uninstaller.

Step 2:  Load up osu!.exe and Revo Uninstaller, set Revo Uninstaller to "Hunter Mode."  With the osu! window visible you should click and drag the Revo Uninstaller crosshairs onto the osu! window.  You will see this pop up:
[img]http://puu.sh/GT7j[/img]

Step 3:  Now what you want to do is go through an advanced uninstall so as to ensure that it will remove all registry keys and files from osu!

Step 4:  I strongly advise to now create a new user account on your computer (or at least change the user name if you're lazy...), and rename your computer name and Workgroup via the System Properties.  
[img]http://puu.sh/GTa8[/img]

Step 5:  [url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=200]Change your IP[/url] address using a method that you know of, this can be done by always using a VPN or Hot Spot Shield, or if you know how to change your IP with your ISP that works also.

Step 6: Change your MAC address using SMAC.  Load up SMAC and select your current network device (or do this to all of them), and randomize the MAC address.

Step 7:  Create a new account on osu, using a NEW email address.

Step 8:  Re-download osu! and install it once more, place your backed up songs and skins in there and you're good to go!


A Few Notes:
I did this after being banned on Kevvv, I created an account called SilverMoon, which lasted for about 2 months, then I created HidingMe which lasted for about 4-5 months.  Both times I got my self banned by cheating to an extent which was rather obvious.

Be cautious with how you cheat!  Don't make it seem obvious.

Copying is prohibited.[/size]

1158.subject: osu!katsudon v2.12 Download and Change Log
1158.message:
This thread here will only contain the most recent version download, and updates with a change log.  

For those who own another bot, you may place this along side with the other program, just make sure that you have Taiko.cfg in the correct place.  Make sure to change the keys in the config so they match your in game settings, if for some reason it is still not hitting correctly, I advise to follow the Song Timer tutorial in the osu! Paid section.


[u][b]Download:[/b][/u]
[url=http://www.theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Taiko/osu!katsudon v2.12.rar]osu!katsudon v2.12[/url]


[u][b]Known Bugs:[/b][/u]
On drumrolls, the bot will most likely miss the last tick (this is currently due to having enough time to hit beats that are extremely close to the end of the drumroll (See: The Big Black).

Some 2-beats sliders are still buggy, still looking into it.

[u][b]Plans:[/b][/u]
Fix all 2-beat sliders.
More customizability on key-hitting patterns.
Add a check that if there is a missing config file, regenerate a default.

[b]Change log:[/b]
[spoiler]
[b]Changes/additions in v2.12 (Aug 4th.):[/b]
Added a thread so that it would run slightly smoother during game play.
Added the note offset from Relax, this has secondary offsets locked to 12.  (Will add a config option to it soon!)
Updated for recent patch also.

[b]Changes/additions in v2.11 (June 21st.):[/b]
Updated for newer song files, hoping that it will extend beyond the current file versions too!

[b]v2.01[/b]
Fixed hitting extra note at end of song.
Fixed slider bugs when close to a timing point.

[b]v2.00[/b]
Added automatic logins with saved details.
Major UI update
Some major fixes with 2-beat sliders
Fixed some inaccuracies during taiko slider calculations making too many hits.
[i]Annie the Eagle is now the head developer of osu!katsudon[/i]

[b]v1.23[/b]
Manual Sliders option, and fixed the slider double key bug.

[b]v1.21[/b]
Better alternating system.
Option for two keys on spinners.
Won't press two keys on big notes if streaming.
Minor Changes.

[b]v1.20[/b]
Faster start up.
Detects spectating and enters Idle Mode.
Detects song speed.
Pausing/skipping supported again.

[b]v1.10[/b]
No memory pointers.
No selecting osu window needed.


[b]v1.00[/b]
Song Timer update method.
Configs work differently.
RandomOffsets added, less chance to be detected.
SpinKeyDownDelay, even less detection chance.

[b]v0.98[/b]
Windows XP supported fully.
Reworked how alternate keys are done.
Added HardRock support.

[b]v0.97[/b]
Reversed how ALT works.  Will now delay.
Minor feature added.  Some users may find this.

[b]v0.96[/b]
Song Percentage.

[b]v0.95[/b]
Update system added.
Detects if the song list has been parsed or not now.
Daily messages displayed, my own way to contact lazy users.

[b]v0.94[/b]
Keys will no longer always alternate.  It will only alternate should the notes be closer than 150ms, calculated to real time.
Added a Right ALT holding feature that will gradually offset the note hits, this will cause a player to miss should they hold it for more than 200ms.
Tweaked HT/DT detection.
Minor improvement.

[b]v0.93[/b]
Fixed slider roll calculations, should be slight errors, but much more reliable now.
Fixed a few slider conversion issues, causing duplicate notes.
Correctly calculates spinners. (Not with HardRock, I need to add in a key for this.)
Removed some issues that would cause the bot to spam keys (Still will send keys when you do not want it to sometimes.)
Tweaked the Rate detection.

[b]v0.91[/b]
Fixed an issue with slider conversions, it was cutting notes out and thus would cause the user to miss notes.
Fixed the bot from spamming thousands of keys after the song was finished but still in "playing" mode.
[/spoiler]

1399.subject: How to set up osu!Relax.  If you have any issues, make sure you've done this.
1399.message:
First of all, if you just bought the subscription, download the bot [url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=84]here[/url].

[b]Step 1[/b]:  Ensure that you have extracted all the files to one folder, please use a tool to hide the program from process lists.

[b]Step 2[/b]:  Load up your osu!Relax and login using your forum username and password.

[b][u]Config explained[/u][/b]:

[b]Window Title[/b]: This is what the window will be called.

[b]Timer Offset[/b]:  This value should be adjusted if you seem to average hitting the note too late or too early.

[b]Random Offsets[/b]:  This value is not nearly as important as Secondary Offsets, but setting this to the same value shouldn't hurt.

[b]Secondary Offsets[/b]:  This value is important if you want to have a legit timing, otherwise you will likely get banned from people viewing the replay.

[b]Key Pattern[/b]:  0 = KeyPresses, 1 = Mouse Clicks, 2 = Key/Mouse

[b]Main Key One[/b]:  This is the primary key you use to press notes, if you have issues, use a number key (0-9).

[b]Main Key Two[/b]:  This is the secondary key you use to press notes, if you have issues, use a number key (0-9).

[b]Normal Key Down Duration[/b]:  This is how long a key will be held down for when not streaming.

[b]Stream Key Down Duration[/b]:  This is how long the keys will be held down while streaming.

[b]Stream Time[/b]:  If the millisecond timing between two notes is less than this, it will stream.

[b]Score Percentage[/b]:  This is how much you want the bot to attempt to score at percentage wise.  Advised to keep it above 90%.

[b]Slider Adjustment[/b]:  This is how much time will be added to hold down sliders.

[b]Spinner Delay[/b]:  This is how long to wait prior to hitting a key down for spinners.

[b]Manual Spinner[/b]:  If ticked, user will have to press keys for the spinners.

[b]Detect Note[/b]:  Checks to make sure your cursor is over the note prior to pressing a key.


If you have gone through all of these issues, please post a thread in the [url=http://www.theaquila.net/forumdisplay.php?fid=25]osu!Relax Issues sub-forum.[/url]  Make sure to read the proper posting format.

1406.subject: How to set up osu!katsudon.  If you have any issues, make sure you've done this!
1406.message:
First of all, if you just bought the subscription, download the bot [url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=105]here[/url].

[b]Step 1[/b]: Ensure that you have extracted all the files to one folder, rename osu!katsudon to something else, this is to combat Peppy's process list checking.

[b]Step 2[/b]: Load up your osu!katsudon and login using your forum username and password.

[b]Step 3[/b]: You may use Ctrl+O to open the config file, the file other wise is located at Data > Configs > Taiko.cfg. This is just a regular text file, just open it using Notepad.

[b]Step 4[/b]: These values are of the most important to ensure are correctly configured right now:

[b]ClickOffset *18* 
[/b]-- This is how many ms early the bot will hit the note, I advise something between 8-20 ms.

[b]NormalKeyDownDuration *40*[/b]
-- How long the bot will keep the key pressed on normal notes. Use anything between 30-40ms to look legit, or use something like 20ms if you're playing a real fast song.  If the value is too low, some slow systems may not hit the key correctly!!!

[b]StreamKeyDownDuration *25*[/b]
-- How long the bot will keep the key pressed while streaming notes. I advise to usually put it around 1/2 of NormalKeyDownDuration.

[b]WindowTitle *Messenger*[/b]
-- This is the title you want the program to go by, combinations of WindowTitle - ProgramName.exe like: Messenger - msn.exe, Task Manager - taskmgr.exe are advised to be safe.

[b]MainRedOne *c* [/b]
-- This is the most used Red Key press.  Currently the only keys supported are 0-9 and a-z.  Use a numerical key if you have issues with a-z keys.
[b]MainRedTwo *x*[/b]
-- This will be the alternate Red Key press.
[b]MainBlueOne *v*[/b]
-- This is the most used Blue Key press.
[b]MainBlueTwo *z*[/b]
-- This will be the alternate Blue Key press.

[b]Step 5[/b]: Save it, and attempt to play a song. If the bot does not hit any keys but detects the song is playing, then you need to find new memory pointers. [url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=192]Here is a link to the thread.[/url]

If you have gone through all of these issues, please post a thread in the osu!katsudon Issues sub-forum. Make sure to read the proper posting format.

1652.subject: osu! Technical Infos
1652.message:
Hi There

This thread is dedicated to information about osu!, the technical aspects of the game. I feel this may be helpful to some people who try to make hacks.
Whenever I discover some new stuff, I'll post it here.

==[ Circle Size ]==
[spoiler]The diameter of a hit circle (diameter, not radius!) in osu pixels can be calculated using the following formula:
96 - Circle Size * 8

Following diameters result:
CS 0: 96 osu px
CS 1: 88 osu px
CS 2: 80 osu px
CS 3: 72 osu px
CS 4: 64 osu px
CS 5: 56 osu px
CS 6: 48 osu px
CS 7: 40 osu px
CS 8: 32 osu px
CS 9: 24 osu px
CS 10: 16 osu px

Funny things to do with this: Write a bot that hits all the circles at their exact border[/spoiler]

==[ Approach Rate ]==
[spoiler]The time in ms until a note starts fading in can be calculated using the following formula:
1950 - Approach Rate * 150

Following Approach Times result:
AR 1: 1800 ms
AR 2: 1650 ms
AR 3: 1500 ms
AR 4: 1350 ms
AR 5: 1200 ms
AR 6: 1050 ms
AR 7: 900 ms
AR 8: 750 ms
AR 9: 600 ms
AR 10: 450 ms[/spoiler]

==[ Overall Difficulty ]==
[spoiler]
The tolerance time in ms can be calculated using the following formulas:
300: 0 to f(x)=80 - OD * 4
100: f(x)=80 - OD * 4 to f(x)=140 - OD * 4
50: f(x)=140 - OD * 4 to f(x)=200 - OD * 4

Following tolerance times result:
OD 0: 300 (0-80), 100 (80-140), 50 (140-200)
OD 1: 300 (0-76), 100 (76-136), 50 (136-196)
OD 2: 300 (0-72), 100 (72-132), 50 (132-192)
OD 3: 300 (0-68), 100 (68-128), 50 (128-188)
OD 4: 300 (0-64), 100 (64-124), 50 (124-184)
OD 5: 300 (0-60), 100 (60-120), 50 (120-180)
OD 6: 300 (0-56), 100 (56-116), 50 (116-176)
OD 7: 300 (0-52), 100 (52-112), 50 (112-172)
OD 8: 300 (0-48), 100 (48-108), 50 (108-168)
OD 9: 300 (0-44), 100 (44-104), 50 (104-164)
OD 10: 300 (0-40), 100 (40-100), 50 (100-160)

NOTE: These values are not tested well enough, confirmation from someone else regarding these is highly appreciated!
[/spoiler]

==[ Stack Leniency ]==
[spoiler]
The maximal time difference two stacked hit objects may have can be calculated using the following formula:
(1950 - Approach Rate * 150) * Stack Leniency
Stacking results in the stacked notes to be moved left and up by x osu px, depending on the circle size.

Offset-Size in osu px
CS 0: 5.16666666666666667
CS 1: 4.83333333333333333
CS 2: 4.5
CS 3: 4
CS 4: 3.5
CS 5: 3.16666666666666667
CS 6: 2.66666666666666667
CS 7: 2.25

I didn't manage to come up with a formula for these values. Ih hope they're correct nonetheless.[/spoiler]

===[ .osu-file-stuff ]===

==[ General ]==
[spoiler]
AudioFilename: obvious.mp3 (string)
AudioLeadIn: time in ms until song starts (f.e. 2000) (int)
PreviewTime: preview point offset in ms (int)
Countdown: whether countdown should be displayed (0=false 1=true) (bool)
SampleSet: Obvious (string)
StackLeniency: Obvious again (float)
Mode: What mode this can be played in (0=Any 1=Taiko 2=CatchTheBeat)
LetterboxInBreaks: Toggles black bars at top and bottom in breaks, 0=false 1=true (bool)
StoryFireInFront: Toggles whether the combo fire is in front of the storyboard 0=false 1=true (bool)
SkinPreference: Skin to be enabled on this map (for some reason there's no space after the colon) (string)
EpilepsyWarning: Toggles whether or not the EpilepsyWarning should be displayed 0=false 1=true (bool)[/spoiler]

==[ Editor ]==
[spoiler]Bookmarks: List of bookmark-offsets in ms, separated by ","
DistanceSpacing: Distance Spacing to use (% of slidermultiplier, 0.5 = half the slider velocity) (double)
BeatDivisor: Beat Snap Divisor to use when the map is loaded up into the editor, 1, 2, 3, 4, 6 and 8 are accepted (int)
GridSize: Size of the grid in osu pixels, uncapped (int)[/spoiler]

==[ Metadata ]==
[spoiler]Title: Obvious (title of the song)
Artist: Obvious (artist of the song)
Creator: The dude who mapped the map
Version: Difficulty name
Source: Source field in editor
Tags: Tags of the map/song[/spoiler]

==[ Difficulty ]==
[spoiler]HPDrainRate: Obvious (int)
CircleSize: Obvious (int)
OverallDifficulty: Obvious, but note that in earlier file format versions of osu! this also determined the approach rate. (int)
ApproachRate: Obvious (int)
SliderMultiplier: Slider Velocity multiplier (double)
SliderTickRate: Obvious (int)[/spoiler]

==[ Events ]==
[spoiler]//Background and Video events: Despite the // makes it look like a comment (at least for developers) it isn't. This is a marker for osu! that these are videos/images that have to be inserted as background (images are f.e. auto-scaled due to this)
//Break Periods: A list of Break-Periods follows after this
2 (id for osu! to know this is a break, int),1044 (startoffset of the break in ms, int),9732 (endoffset of the break in ms, int)

//Storyboard Layer 0 (Background): Obvious
//Storyboard Layer 1 (Fail): Obvious
//Storyboard Layer 2 (Pass): Obvious
//Storyboard Layer 3 (Foreground): Obvious
//Storyboard Sound Samples: Obvious
//Background Colour Transformations: 
3 (id for osu! to know this is a BG Color Transformation, int),100 (ms offset for the transformation to take place, int),0 (red value, byte),0 (blue value, byte),0 (green value, byte)

The topmost transformation will be the default Background Color, regardless of what value you set, other transformations take place at the time you set them.
3,5000,255,0,0
3,3000,255,255,255

This will start as red, after three seconds turn to white, at second 5 turn to red for a moment, then back to white again.[/spoiler]

==[ TimingPoints ]==
[spoiler]
Two types have to be generally considered: Non-Inherited and Inherited.

Non-Inherited:
54(offset, int),413.793103448276(ms per beat, double),4 (time signature, int),2 (sampleset 1=normal 2=soft),1 (custom sampleset 0=default 1=custom1 2=custom2),70 (volume, int),1 (non-inherited, bool),0 (kiai, bool)

Inherited:
4812 (offset, int),-100 (slidermultiplier*, int),4 (time signature),2 (sampleset 1=normal 2=soft),1 (custom sampleset 0=default 1=custom1 2=custom2),60 (volume, int),0 (non-inherited, bool),0 (kiai, bool)

* Slider Multiplier:
x1 = -100
x2 = -50
x0.5 = -200
Formula: -100 / value
-100 / -100 = 1
-100 / -50 = 2
-100 / -200 = 0.5

Any value can be set, even those that exceed 2.0 and 0.5, but they have to be set manually by editing the .osu-file (osu! does not crash or hardcap these)[/spoiler]

==[ Colours ]==
[spoiler]Combo1 : 252 (red value, byte),201 (blue value, byte),142 (green value, byte)

Combo1 up to Combo8 work fine, all others will be ignored, but won't cause the map to break.[/spoiler]

==[ HitObjects ]==
[spoiler]
Hit-Circle:
256 (x-coord, int),192 (y-coord, int),54 (ms offset, int),117 (type*, int),0 (hitsound)

*types:
1, 5, 21, 37, 53, 69, 85, 101, 117 = Hit-Circle
2, 6, 22, 38, 54, 70, 86, 102, 118 = Slider
8, 12, 28, 44, 60, 76, 92, 108, 124 = Spinner

Slider:
180 (head-x, int),116 (head-y, int),260 (ms offset, int),2 (type, int),0 (hitsound),B|256:172 (control-points),2 (amount of times the path is slided along (2=1 repetition),79.9999999999999 (length in osu px)

Sliders are the most shitty thing in osu! Files to read out.
I recommend you check out roughly what a bezir curve is now if you intend to understand sliders.
Control Points: Control Point #1 is always the head of the slider.
The other control points are defined separately. The least amount of control points a slider can have are 2 (the head and another one somewhere else).
Sliders have following cases:
2 Control Points: Line-Slider, just a straight line, easiest, simplest form.
3 Control Points: Quadratic Bezir Slider, a simple quadratic bezir.
4 Control Points: Cubic Bezir Slider, a simple cubic bezir.
>3 Control Points: The Slider curve is calculated by taking the first 4 points, drawing a small section of a cubic bezir along those 4 points (I believe around 15-20% of that bezir is drawn), then taking another 4 points, the first point is the last point of the bezir part previously drawn, then from that point onward it takes the second, third and fourth control point, and repeats that over and over until it reaches the last 4 points, from where it draws a full cubic bezir curve.

All sliders are drawn like this, double points count as end-points. 

I hope this explanation was understandable and helped you :)

Spinner:
256 (x-coord, int, can be ignored),192 (y-coord, int, can be ignored),674 (ms-offset, int),12 (type, int),0 (hitsound),1812 (ms-offset of the end of the spinner, int)[/spoiler]

==[ Miscellaneous Infos ]==
[spoiler]Whenever osu! submits a score to the web, a list of your currently running processes is sent alongside the score, so incase you intend to bot, rename your bots to something casual, f.e. firefox.exe.

osu! Seems to be reading out your PCs name to detect whether you are a banned player, and you might be banned again if you do not change this after you have been banned.[/spoiler]

==[ TODO ]==
[spoiler]-Detailed info about the drain
-Detailed info about how mods affect things
-Detailed info about how Overall Difficulty was handled before it was separated into OD and AR
-Find out about all pre-defined storyboarding toggles/values[/spoiler]

==[ About ]==
[spoiler]
This is about everything I know about how the game technically works.
I hope this information might help certain persons trying to create hacks/bots/whatever.

I discovered all this information solely by experimenting and looking at the game. It may be partly wrong or inaccurate, but as far as my tests have gone, pretty much all of these informations have been exact and right enough.

If you know something I didn't mention here, or if you feel something is missing, please add the information as a response to this or PM me about it, but please make sure to test whether your information is correct as good as you can.
[/spoiler]
==[ Changelog ]==
[spoiler]
28/7 Posted
28/7 First update, restructured a little bit, added TODO and Changelog
28/7 Added bunch of stuff I was originally too lazy to add
28/7 Added spoilers
28/7 Added some info about Overall Difficulty; Confirmation appreciated!
30/7 Corrected misinformation about stack leniency[/spoiler]

Over and Out, SteakJohnson

1666.subject: RE: Spinner hack
1666.message:
Technically how to make this work and look somewhat legit:
Get the current cursors position
Click if the mouse button isnt already being held
Get the distance from the cursors position to (256,192) of the osu! playing area
Get the angle from (256,192) of the osu! playing area to the cursor position
Set this as your starting angle.
Reduce the distance over time up to a minimum of say, 5-25 px (the minimum is randomly set when this routine begins)
Increase the angle over time (2520/second should be somewhat over 400)
Once the minimum distance is reached, start adding random values ranging from maybe 5-10 osu px to this, so it isn't a perfect circle.

Happy testing out, I'm too lazy to turn these thoughts into a working program :)

Over and Out, SteakJohnson

1680.subject: How to use osu!TimeWarp.  Use this if you don't know what you're doing.
1680.message:
There really is not a whole bunch that can go wrong with this program. 

To start you will want to load up osu! and start a song, then you can go back to menu.  Load up osu!TimeWarp, TimeWarp will patch osu! if it has not been patched before.  After that you should be free to play and song and use the assigned hotkeys.


This program requires you to edit the config prior to loading it, [u]there is no config reloading feature.[/u]

Open up the config at "Data\Configs\TimeWarp.cfg", just use [b]Notepad[/b] to view it.


[u][b]WindowTitle *SETTHISTOSOMETHING*[/b][/u]
This is what the window title of the program will be displayed as while running.
Rename the .exe to something like msn.exe and use Messenger as the title...  Make it look like a legit program running in the background.
*STRONGLY ADVISED TO CHANGE THIS*

[u][b]PercentChange *5.0* [/b][/u]
Every time you hit a key that will change the song speed, this is how much it will change by.  5% seemed to be fine for me.

[b]DecreaseSpeed *u*[/b]
[b][u]IncreaseSpeed *i*[/u][/b]
Keys that are used to change the speed of the song.

[u][b]SpinnerSpeed *90.00*[/b][/u]
This is a percentage for the song speed when spinners are active (Used for legit spinner cheating).  If you don't know what to do, you should probably leave this at 90%.
(When doubletime is active, the spinner speed will increase by an additional 50%.  Ex: 90% becomes 140%.)

[u][b]How to use Anti-Bancho[/b][/u]
[list]
[*]You must be logged in prior to doing anything.
[*]Tick the Bancho Begone! box.
[*]Proceed to login on the osu! client.
[*]Wait until you see [img]http://puu.sh/39sbu/e76837c6dc.jpg[/img]
[*]Hit the X button to close the login window.
[*]Play a song and it will submit!
[/list]

1681.message:
[align=center]

[b][u]Description:[/u][/b]
This is a speed hack for osu! it can make the song play at 1%-400%, and still submit a score.
This works for ALL game modes.

1847.subject: RE: osu!Relax v2.35 Download and Change Log
1847.message:
Ye i just noticed that after i posted and i was too lazy to edit my post + i was not sure :D

-Edit- So if you dont want to download it again, make sure your config looks like that:
TimerOffsetOne *0x88*
TimerOffsetTwo *0x1F0*
TimerOffsetThree *0xBC*
TimerOffsetFour *0x6D4*
TimerOffsetFive *0x40*
TimerDLLOffset *0x000B4950*
TimerDLLName *Microsoft.Xna.Framework.dll*
ClickOffset *9*				// This value is in ms
NormalKeyDownDuration *60*
StreamKeyDownDuration *50*
WindowTitle *CGVPN*	// This is the title you want the program to go by.
MainKeyOne *h*		// This is the key you hit the most.
MainKeyTwo *j*		// This is the key you use to stream with.
ScorePercentage *100.00* // Set this to have the program attempt to score around this percentage.
RandomOffsets *0*	 	// This works in either way, so 15ms will be a 30ms window!

1952.subject: How to find the offsets.  (No video at the moment.)
1952.message:
To sum it up, the way to find a new memory address if the error is appearing would be:

1:  Start the song, with Cheat engine scan for "0".
2:  Enable speedhack and set it to "5", play the song until error shows.
3:  Pause instantly as the error shows.
4:  Scan for "-500", if nothing appears "Undo Scan" and scan for "-499"
5:  You will have one address left.  Do a complete Pointer Scan for this, similar to [url=http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=97]osu!Relax.[/url]

My best advice after updates go out will be to use the newly downloaded files.

2167.subject: Song Timer Assisting programs.
2167.message:
I made these programs to assist in finding the memory pointer for many users.  It appears to be difficult for people.

[b]You will need:[/b]
[url=http://www.theaquila.net/Programs/AssistPrograms.rar]The two programs.[/url]
Cheat Engine 6.2
osu! (;P)



[b]-Step 1-[/b]
Create a folder on your desktop and extract the two programs in the .rar file to that folder.

[b]-Step 2-[/b]
Create a shortcut to osu! in that same folder you created.
Create a shortcut to Cheat Engine in that same folder.
The names should be:
"Cheat Engine"
"osu!"

Should look like:
[img]http://puu.sh/YLeT[/img]

[b]-Step 3-[/b]
Load up osu! and ensure you are logged out of your account, and you are in windowed mode.
Exit osu!.

[b]-Step 4-[/b]
Run First.exe and wait, there will be a couple times that it requires your input during the procedure.
Restart after the Pointer Scan is completed.

[b]-Step 5-[/b]
You should now only need Second.exe, load that and wait.
The program will need your input a few times here.  Having done so, it should have re-scanned your pointer scan correctly.

Unless you have 4-20 Pointers left, I advise re-doing Step 5.

2350.subject: RE: rank not recorded!
2350.message:
Pointers aren't needed.

If you are having trouble with the timing in songs here is some things you should know.

Do NOT push skip button at the start of a song.
Do NOT pause the song at all
If you are playing with double time change the speed to 1.5(ctrl e)
If you are playing with half time change the speed to .75(ctrl e)

If the timing is off and you have corrected everything above then you need to change some settings.

ClickOffset *10* // Change this anywhere from 5 to 30, depending on the song
RandomOffsets *10* // Default is 15 but I prefer 10 for better timings.

Most songs I play with a ClickOffset of 10-20, if that doesn't work then you just have to try different numbers.

*I have noted with v2.50 that there are a FEW songs that I can't seem to get timed correctly, its best you just ignore them for now.  (http://osu.ppy.sh/b/96765 on insane for example)

Current Features:
Flashlight hack
Hidden hack
Universal Approach Rate (Basically a HR hack)


[u][b]How to use[/b]:[/u]
Start osu! (You can not be logged in, you must be a Guest)
Start a song with Hidden (Flashlight too if you wish to patch for Flashlight also)
Go back to the menu.
Start Enlighten and patch for what you want accordingly.
[b]Important:[/b] If you are patching for Hidden, go to the mod screen and Reset All Mods, if the score multiplier is not 1.06x, [u]repatch Hidden![/u].
Once you have patched for everything you want close Enlighten and Login to your account.

[i]Note: If you want to specify a millisecond value for Approach Rate, enter 1337 for the AR value first and it will then ask for a millisecond value.[/i]

suggested.

S Ranker - Get S or SS Ranks on 3 maps consecutively.

Obsessed, Nonstop and Jack of All Trades

My friend unlocked the Jack of All Trades because he can play every game mode efficiently and masterfully.

EDIT:

How to get "Stumbler"

1. Download [url=http://osu.ppy.sh/s/1208]this[/url] map.
2. Play the "Beginner" diff. and enable the "SuddenDeath" mod.
3. While playing the map, change song offset to "110ms"
3. Play the map like you usually do but time your clicking to the beat of the song so that you will get all 100's.
4. Pass the map.
5. Congratz! You haz Stumbler achievement.

I made this so that people don't have to act like a total noob player to get this achievement (trust me, i did that and my head hurts doing so.) Thnx to WhoCares? for the way of getting the achievement.

Follow the steps in http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=100
once your ip and mac address and computer name are changed, make a new osu! account.

go to program files and create a folder called Diablo III
extract relax bot and rename it to Diablo III *create a shorcut and put it on desktop

2419.subject: RE: After a few seconds, fails everywhere
2419.message:
If you are having trouble with the timing in songs here is some things you should know.

Do NOT push skip button at the start of a song.
Do NOT pause the song at all
If you are playing with double time change the speed to 1.5(ctrl e)
If you are playing with half time change the speed to .75(ctrl e)

If the timing is off and you have corrected everything above then you need to change some settings.

ClickOffset *10* // Change this anywhere from 5 to 30, depending on the song
RandomOffsets *10* // Default is 15 but I prefer 10 for better timings.

Most songs I play with a ClickOffset of 10-20, if that doesn't work then you just have to try different numbers.

*I have noted with v2.50 that there are a FEW songs that I can't seem to get timed correctly, its best you just ignore them for now. (http://osu.ppy.sh/b/96765 on insane for example)

2435.subject: Playcount Increaser - WhoCares?
2435.message:
So, you should use [url=http://www.ghost-control.com/download.html]Ghost Control[/url] to record yourself playing the beginning of a map (sth like 30 combo), press "Start recording".
The free version can only record 30 seconds.

[b]What you should be recording is[/b]:

[list]
[*]Pressing Enter to start the map;
[*]Playing the map;
[*]Pressing Escape and clicking on "Back to menu";
[/list]

Then, end the recording(Esc or Pause on your keyboard). 
Now, you should see your record in "My jobs", click on "Repeat" and choose how many times you want to repeat it.
[img]http://puu.sh/1019s[/img]

Btw, you should play the map with No fail because the record and the map won't be synchronised on first try but it will be on second.
[size=small][color=#FF0000][b]Use this program only to increase playcount! You would lose account, if you want to rank your map played with it![/b][/color][/size]

2524.subject: RE: osu!Relax Doubletime Issue
2524.message:
If you are playing with double time change the speed to "1.5"(ctrl+e)
If you are playing with half time change the speed to ".75"(ctrl+e)

There was wrong in your timings...
In your config copy this! 

ClickOffset *10*	 // This value is in ms
NormalKeyDownDuration *80*
StreamKeyDownDuration *40*
WindowTitle *Windows Live Messenger*	 // This is the title you want the program to go by.
MainKeyOne *x*	 // This is the key you hit the most.
MainKeyTwo *z*	 // This is the key you use to stream with.
ScorePercentage *100.00* // Set this to have the program attempt to score around this percentage.
RandomOffsets *15*	 // This works in either way, so 15ms will be a 30ms window!

change your windowtittle to prevent being banned and to submit scores..
EX: "utorrent.exe"
Also to be safer. Osu! takes the whole directory of the running programs in memory, I advice to put your hack in "Program files"..

That's all you need!!!! :P

And how to use in Osu?Can someone Teach meh pls :(

Sorry bad English.
[/quote]

Open up osu and then open up ghost control. Locate the "Start Recording" button located in the bottom right corner. I suggest you have the countdown to recording on. 

Press the record button, and then play the map you want ghost control to replay. (please note that Ghost Control's free version can only record up to 30 seconds, meaning that playing through a whole map is unfeasible.) 

When finished go to your jobs tab, and then run the job you just recorded.

I believe Ghost Control may play it back offset-ted slightly, play it once more and it shouldn't be.

I hope this helps.


EDIT: Ghost control IS bannable. use wisely
