2854.subject: [Picture Guide] How to find your Position Offsets
2854.message:
I know many users will have issues with this in the long run...

These things in the config are a tad bit difficult to obtain for new users...
[spoiler]
PositionOffsetOne *0x580*
PositionOffsetTwo *0x2E4*
PositionOffsetThree *0x554*
PositionOffsetFour *0x78*
PositionOffsetFive *0xA4*
PositionOffsetSix *0xB8*
PositionDLLOffset *0x000B4950*
PositionDLLName *Microsoft.Xna.Framework.dll*
[/spoiler]

Thus I will be including as many pictures as I can!

[u][b]Things You Will Need:[/b][/u]
Cheat Engine (I use 6.2)
osu! ( ;3 )
About an hour of your time.  (It took me 2 hours to make this guide...)

[u]Step 1[/u]
First you will want to load osu! and Cheat Engine (I advise you don't stay logged into osu!.)
Then attach Cheat Engine to osu!.exe, this picture will help:
[img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/1.png[/img]

([u][b]This is how you will be finding your position address.[/b][/u])
You will be pointer scanning for it soon, just remember you will have to find the position address another time.

[u]Step 2[/u]
Load up a Catch the Beat song, WITH NO FAIL, and wait (DO NOT MOVE) until the first note/fruit has passed.
Pause osu! and go back to Cheat Engine.
You will be scanning for a float value of 256.0, as shown in this image:
[img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/2.png[/img]

[u]Step 3[/u]
After the scan finishes, go back to osu! and move your character all the way to the left.
Pause osu! and go back to Cheat Engine, your Next Scan should be for the value 0.0.
Here is another image:
[img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/3.png[/img]

[i]If there is not one value in your list, go back to osu! and move your character to the right all the way.
Then scan for 512.0[/i]

There should be one value, this value changes as you move your character.  Double click it and it will appear in the bottom list of addresses.

[i]We have now found the address, this is where we will start the pointer scan.[/i]

[u]Step 4[/u]
Right click that address in the bottom list, and select "Pointer scan for this address".
Here is another image for you:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/4.png[/img][/spoiler]

A new window will pop up, and you will want to use these settings:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/5.png[/img][/spoiler]
And hit "OK"

It will prompt you to save the file somewhere, save it, but [u]make sure you know where it is[/u], and call it "First".
We will be loading this file shortly!
Wait for the scan to finish now.

[u]Step 5[/u]
(My first scan had 2,177,000,000 found.)
Restart your computer.
I know it sucks, but just do it so that this is faster.  :3

[u]Step 6[/u]
Load up osu! and Cheat Engine again, and find the position address like you just did (Stop after Step 3, [b]don't do Step 4 or 5[/b].)


[u]Step 7[/u]
Click the "Memory View" button on Cheat Engine.  A new window will pop up, select "Tools">"Pointer Scan."
Another Image:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/7.png[/img][/spoiler]

On that new window "Pointer Scan", select File>Open, and open that file you created in Step 4.

[u]Step 8[/u]
Now click the "Pointer Scanner" menu, and select "Rescan memory - Removes pointers not pointing to the right address".
Enter the current Address for your character position.
Another Image:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/8.png[/img][/spoiler]

Hit OK, and save the file as "Second"
Now wait...

[u]Step 9[/u]
I still had more addresses at this point...
Go back to osu!, exit the song, and start up another song and pause it.
On the Pointer Scan Window click "Pointer Scanner" and select "Rescan memory - Removes pointers not pointing to the right address".
We will now scan "Value to find:"
Make sure the value type is Float, and you are scanning for 256.0.
Image:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/9.png[/img][/spoiler]


[u]Step 10[/u]
At this point I had only 700 addresses, it was enough to find one that said "Microsoft.Xna.Framework.dll"
Then I was able to do the config as follows:
[spoiler][img]http://theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Catch/Guide/10.png[/img][/spoiler]

[size=Large][align=center][color=#FFFFFF]Catch the Beat Bot - Work in progress[/color][/align][/size]

[size=medium][b][color=#FFFFFF]Creator's words[/color][/b][/size]

     First of all I'm only showing one new (and first "hack") that I've coded for Osu!, I Don't have any interest to compete with Kev. But I [u]only want to show[/u] My Hack.

[b]Language used to code:[/b] Delphi (Object Pascal)
[b]Hours coding:[/b] 5 Hours (In Pre-Alpha stage, from 0 to working status)
[b]Functionality: [/b]Is working well but some things need to be done.
[b]Sliders:[/b] 0% (I will start code this part next days or next week I think)
[b]Spinners: [/b]0% (Planning one Schema for catch arround 100% or X% Bannanas)
[b]How Spinners will work:[/b] In config tab will have the option for select how much percent of bananas want to catch, and the bot will catch.

[size=Medium][b][color=#FFFFFF]Program interface[/color][/b][/size]
[img]http://puu.sh/1vlBc[/img]

[b]Debug information[/b] tab returns to user some messages such as erros and the progress of bot. Like as current beat time, Song started, Bot stopped.

[b]Configs[/b] tab It's for configuration, for now only can set offsets, the "fine adjust" is for users who like more precision or want make bot do 99,57%, 98%, etc, instead 100%

[color=#FFFFFF][size=medium][b]Finally the video demo[/b][/size][/color]
[video=youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zAkS__dBUpU[/video]

Sorry for my bad english, thanks for watching and thanks for feedback.

3820.subject: Suggestion on key press behaviour
3820.message:
Could you allow for an option to change the key press behaviour?

As of current it uses 1 key for most notes and then both keys for streams but without this program I usually play alternating both keys at all times (Like K1 > K2 > K1 > K2 etc throughout the whole song).

The more common method of both keys only for streams would look odd to the people that know me well if they watch my replays of this. (And I'm not sure whether Osu could check for this change in behaviour to how I usually play.. a little paranoid about it).

I know this is likely an issue which only effects few of us (or probably just me >-<) so I don't expect much of a response to this request.

If not that, am I safe if I just ensure I do not rank higher than #40 on maps so people can't check my replays? Or is Osu! capable of noticing a change in behaviour with key presses?

3865.subject: Multiboxxing, sandboxie, etc
3865.message:
I know for a fact I am not the only person to do this. I used 2 computers each running a different copy of Osu!. I linked my one mouse + 1 keyboard to both of them with Input Director. I would play HD+FL on one PC while normal on the other. In return, it was like a perfect HD+FL hack, but well not perfect. There is a little bit of lag between the 2 PC's so getting 100% accuracy is impossibly on OD8-10.

I have a theory that if you use sandboxie to run a second copy of Osu, there is no need of a second PC therefor, with the correct software, there is no lag. I personally have 2 monitors, so I'd have one Osu on each monitor. The only problem is software. I need to find a way to have both Osu's react to the same KB+M. I'm having difficulty figuring this out. If anyone else can help, that would be great :)

Also, I don't believe this is even possible to detect, and if you edit a map and lower the AR on the osu copy you will actually play on, you can turn this into a HR hack as well if you can't read AR10+.

3867.subject: Hush Hush Achievements Guide
3867.message:
I made this to help anyone using google. The last thread sure helped me :)

[img]http://i.imgur.com/Sle6g.jpg[/img]

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Hopping Bunny[/b][/u][/size][/color]
This secret achievement requires you to full combo "Chatmonchy - Make Up! Make Up!" beatmap by peppy, creator of Osu! The title of this achievement is obvious when you play through the beatmap.

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]S-Ranker[/b][/u][/size][/color]
To unlock this secret achievement, simply receive an S rank three times in a row on different maps. The safest way is to plan 3 maps you already know you can full combo with over 95% accuracy and play them all in a row.

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Most Improved[/b][/u][/size][/color]
1. Play a new mapset you never played before and get a really bad score. Like 50% accuracy
2. Play it again and full combo that same diff.
3. Repeat on 10-20 different maps.

Tip: you can not have played any of those maps before. You also only have just one shot per mapset. No retries.

You have to do this multiple times (10-20 times) for it to give you the achievement.

Video Tutorial + Proof: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GHPzw3UHCWs
(read the creators comments)

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Non-Stop Dancer[/b][/u][/size][/color]
To unlock this secret achievement, simply play any ranked or approved beatmap that is longer than ten minutes and pass without easy/no-fail/Halftime mods. To find beatmaps this long, search "marathon" in the beatmap search bar.

I got it from this:
http://osu.ppy.sh/s/972
I can't read low AR so I used HR.  Also OD+HPDR is pretty low so it's possible to use this map to get this achievement and Consilation Prize at the same time. If you can manage to FC this with a low %, you can get stumbler and Nonstop at the same time too. 4 achievements at once :P

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][b][u]Consolation Prize[/u][/b][/size][/color]
Pass the hardest difficulty of any ranked mapset with below a 70% without no-fail and/or easy mods. This is extremely difficult to do as most insane difficulties make it impossible to pass under a 70%. A trick is to tweak your universal offset so your accuracy will be lower ingame even if you feel your playing normally. Then find a ranked mapset which the hardest difficulty is 'Hard' or lower.

from boko:
I recommend this map for Consolation Prize
osu.ppy.sh/b/1147
It's difficult, yet very forgiving (low HP drain).

Note: It's very likely that you can not have played the mapset at all before doing this.

Tested in mania : does not work in it. It's probably standard only.

Video Tutorial/Proof: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1gJB0ZTHKG0

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][b][u]Challenge Accepted[/u][/b][/size][/color]
Im not 100% sure since I already had this achievement and I wasnt sure how I got it. I heard its from simply passing an Approved map, but there might be more to it than that.


[color=#1E90FF][size=large][b][u]Stumbler[/u][/b][/size][/color]
Full combo any difficulty on any ranked beatmap set with a D ranking. The easiest way to manage this is to tweak the universal offset and play a ranked beatmap on easy with sudden death.

Note: It's very likely that you can not have played the mapset at all before doing this.

Video proof: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QtkA9Fu5lm0

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][b][u]Quick Draw[/u][/b][/size][/color]
Be the first person to pass any difficulty of a newly ranked mapset in any playmode. (found this on teamliquid's forum. I tried it on mania and it doesn't seem to work there. Maybe ctb+taiko+standard only).

Tip: Keep an eye on #announce for newly ranked maps and quickly download it as soon as it's ranked. Nofail+DT the shortest diff.

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Obsessed[/b][/u][/size][/color]
Play the same map over 100 times in the same day. Retries count (but it has to be a certain amount of time into the map to count). The best way to do this is to attempt to FC a normal/hard difficulty with the Perfect mod enabled.

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Jack Of All Trades[/b][/u][/size][/color]
5,000 plays of each game mode. Not sure if mania counts in this.

[color=#FFD700][size=large][u][b]Jackpot[/b][/u][/size][/color]
Achieve a score of exactly 7,777,777
proof from boko:
http://cdn-ak.f.st-hatena.com/images/fotolife/A/AyoshiA/20120825/20120825223913.jpg
proof from kev:
http://puu.sh/1zeVl

I guess just use nofail on a long song and once you get close, be careful. If you happen to get to 7,777,777 just wait for the song to end and now you can brag to everyone on #osu :3

[color=#1E90FF][size=large][u][b]Nonstop[/b][/u][/size]
[/color]One theory for Nonstop is to FC a 10 minute or longer map. Please post any ranked/approved 10+ minute playtime maps that are easy. Most are generally difficult or extremely long.


[size=large][u][b]Conclusion[/b][/u][/size]
Well there ya have it. A guide for the secret achievements. I'll continue updating this as I can. If you know of any ranked/approved maps in the following categories, please post them :)
[list]
[*] Easy Approved maps
[*] Maps longer than 10 minutes and are not difficult (normal/hard diffs)
[*] Mapsets which hardest diff is easy to get consolation prize in (low HPDR)
[/list]

If you find something wrong with this guide, or got a useful tip, please let me know!

Play a map, get a really bad score, then improve it by a tenfold. The best way to do this is to play bad on purpose with the half time mod on a map you can normally full combo. Play the map again and full combo it like normally to unlock this secret achievement.

[img]http://i.imgur.com/DbE0W.png[/img]
To unlock this secret achievement, simply play any ranked or approved beatmap that is longer than ten minutes and pass without easy/no-fail/Halftime mods. To find beatmaps this long, search "marathon" in the beatmap search bar.

[img]http://i.imgur.com/e6HcO.png[/img]
Pass the hardest difficulty of any ranked mapset with below a 70% without no-fail and/or easy mods. [img]http://i.imgur.com/mTTXy.png[/img]
Full combo any difficulty on any ranked beatmap set with a D ranking. The easiest way to manage this is to tweak the universal offset and play a ranked beatmap on easy with the sudden death mod on.

[img]http://i.imgur.com/7eiFf.png[/img]

[img]http://i.imgur.com/hkEmW.png[/img]
Play the same map over 100 times in the same day. Retries count. The best way to do this is to attempt to reach the top 40 leaderboards on a normal/hard difficulty with the Perfect mod enabled.

[u][b]Jack Of All Trades[/b][/u] (reached 10 image limit lol)
Play every game mode efficiently. The skill/amount of times played needed is unknown, but play enough of each and this secret achievement will be unlocked eventually. But just as an example, White Wolf has a 672 playcount in CtB, 2,803 in Taiko, and 120,262 in standard and does not have this achievement. TTTL is in the top 100 ranks for both standard and Taiko, but is ranked in the 4000 in CtB and does not have this achievement. However, Uan is in the top 500 for each of the 3 modes and he got the achievement. It's probably really hard to get.


Jackpot & Nonstop are the only ones unknown to me. Nonstop might be like Obsessed but maybe more than 1000 tries instead? Or maybe it's just playing nonstop for a very long period of time like 12 hours? I literally have no idea what jackpot could be.
[/quote]

wonderful contribution good sir

3976.subject: The client ban problem
3976.message:
I am one of the guys who got the PM by dan013 to avoid the insta client ban in osu!.
I now want to share this with you (don't spam dan anymore).
Note that I did not had the idea, all credits go to dan.
Thank him.

So, there are two different ways in order to not get client banned.

The 1st is to create a Virtual Hard Drive (VHD) and install osu! on it.
You can find a very detailed tutorial here: 
http://www.howtogeek.com/howto/5291/how-to-create-a-virtual-hard-drive-in-windows-7/
The VHD will "delete" after you reboot your computer.
But don't worry. You don't have to do this every time you reboot your computer. You can just chose to attach the VHD once you have created it.
(http://puu.sh/1Acsr - click attach instead of create here and chose the the one where osu is installed on)
This is the methoid I am using and probably the easier one.

The 2nd one is to use a program called "Sandboxie" which you can download here: http://www.sandboxie.com/
I did never use this method and that's why I can't really tell if its good or not. You may want to read the Help and FAQ part on this webiste if you are having troubles with this program.
Just launch osu via the Sandboxie Client. I'll just trust dan that it works perfectly fine aswell.


However, dont forget: You still have to change your IP (http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=200) and Mac Adresse (via a cracked Version of SMAC or other programs you may know).

I hope this is detailed enough and my English isn't too bad today so you can understand this :D
If you have and further questions just PM me. I will try my best to figure out why it didnt work for you.

A mod may move this thread to "Tutorials Plus". I got an Error and couldn't post it there.

Have fun with osu and don't stop hacking :D

Legit movement issues.

[spoiler]
[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.22 (Jul 14th):[/b]
Updated for the most recent patch, added some functionality if anyone were to ever use with TimeWarp... I hope no one does.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.21 (Jul 14th):[/b]
Added a check to see if the program has been ran as SYSTEM using veiled.
Fixed issues with not being able to use other movements.
Fixed an error with server authentications.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.20 (Jul 10th):[/b]
Added a legit movement beta.  Please do give me your feedback!

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.10 (May 15th):[/b]
Updated for latest osu!
Added song reset detection?  (I'm surprised I hadn't added that.)
Improved in play detection (using threads like relax.)
New GUI for play.
New login GUI/system that supports spaces in username and symbols in passwords.
Fixed having an extra config in the compressed folder.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.04 (May 15th):[/b]
Temp security system.
v12 osu files supported.
Added the mini GUI.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.03 (Mar 1st):[/b]
Added Circle movements, Mouse Assist is now 2 and circle auto is 1.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.02 (Feb 12th):[/b]
Removed a text display function left in there for debugging.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.01 (Feb 11th):[/b]
Fixed a stacking issue with sliders.
Made Hard Rock into a toggle.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v1.00:[/b]
New CUI.
Relax option for Full Auto added for users with a Relax Subscription. (This is one key clicking, users must use "x".)
Fixed a bug regarding the song timer being offset.
Fixed slow movements on Windows 8.

[b]Fixes/additions and released in v0.90:[/b]
Initial release.

[/spoiler]

4063.subject: For those with the Error when parsing songs.
4063.message:
I have created a new SongParser.exe which will allow a user to fix their issues.

[url=http://www.theaquila.net/Announcements/RandomProjects/SongParser.rar]Download Here[/url]

Place these two files into the Data folder of the bot and open up the SongParser.cfg.

Make the file look like this:

[code]
$Directory = "Q:\Program Files (x86)\osu!\Songs"   	
$UseCustomDirectory=1    				
[/code]

You put your own osu! song directory and set UseCustomDirectory to 1 and the error won't occur anymore.

4103.subject: How to use osu!Auto.
4103.message:
[align=center][size=large][b][u]Config Options:[/u][/b][/size]

[b]WindowTitle *Beta*[/b]
This is what the programs window title will display as.  It is advised that you store the bot in a legit looking program files folder.

[b]TimerOffset *-9*[/b]
TimerOffset is just an offset for the bot when playing the song.  I like to keep it around -10 to 0 so it approaches the note early.

[b]TimeToWaitOnNote *30*[/b]
This feature is only for mouse assist at the moment, it tells the bot how long of a window it should sit on the note.  If set to 30ms, it will stay at the note 15ms before and 15ms after you should hit it.

[b]MouseMoveType *1*[/b]
This determines which type of movement you will be using:
0 is Full Auto.
1 is Circle Auto.
2 is Mouse Assist. (You should train with this before ranking.)
3 is reserved for legit movements.

[b]MouseAssistStrength *0.40*[/b]
This is how strong the mouse assist will function, a higher number creates a straighter line.

[b]MouseAssistPower *1*[/b]
This is how the mouse assist fades in.  A higher number here will make mouse assist only function closer to the note time.

[b]MouseAssistDistanceStop *20*[/b]
This is the distance at which mouse assist will no longer function around the center of note.[/align]

4184.subject: RE: The client ban problem
4184.message:
The best way to evade a ban: Get an IRL friend to play osu for a while, he/she must be totally new at it.
Give that person some time until he/she stops playing.
Ask for account.
Get an external hard drive, copy your friend's osu copy, change your computer's username to the one that your friend had (written in one of the cfg files).
Ask your internet service provider for an IP reset/change.
Profit.

Or something much more effective:
Get a new computer and switch internet services.

QUICK EDIT:
The ban takes place AFTER you quit the osu client, not as you log in!

4332.subject: RE: osu!Enlighten, free for subscribers (FL/HD hack.)
4332.message:
Well Peppy is either too scared to ban me, or he's still unable to detect this as long as it's used responsibly.

There's no real confirmation of there being an autoban system in place which detects your playstyle as being unusual but I'm going to assume there isn't. Also there doesn't seem to be an autoban system in place which is capable of detecting the functionality of this mod else I would be banned by now.

So I'll assume that bans are done manually and the administration doesn't have time to monitor thousands of users so they're likely only monitoring through replays in the top 40, and most likely only of which are very obvious or have been reported.

Some advice to avoid a ban:

Don't ever visit theaquila.net while the Osu! client is open.

Wouldn't recommend ever trying to rank #1 with cheats on, even if you do have a playcount of 100+ on that map. The legitimacy of your replay isn't always checked, someone may report your score out of spite even when you do play without cheats (I know of people who have been banned just for ranking first on a map without cheating - because their name isn't familiar for ranking first).

Personally my highest ranking was 2nd, I did get rank #1 on a new insane map once because I forgot that HD mod was on - my only 'oh shit' moment. In order to make it look more legitimate I played the same map with HD mod about 20 or so more times., luckily I wasn't #1 on that map for long. xD

Getting FC with either HD OR FL is more like than getting FC with both HD AND FL. Only use both on maps that are sure to be possible with both (and have been cleared previously by people using both). Also, never be the first on a map to rank high with FL, especially not insane maps (and ranking with FL on insane maps is pushing it).

Ensure that in your profile, your minimum playcount in the list of most played maps is 100+ or at least 50+. You're less likely to be reported because other users will be unable to assume that you got a good ranking in a minimal amount of plays. Generally, it's easy enough to rank with HD on most maps with just 10 to 20 plays, much more required for FL on harder maps.

I'd also recommend your account be at least 6 months old or else you may be reported for multi-account considering it's unlikely for someone to be capable of playing with mods in their first few months of playing. 4390.subject: RE: osu!Enlighten, free for subscribers (FL/HD hack.)
4390.message:
[quote='boko' pid='4332' dateline='1358326886']
Well Peppy is either too scared to ban me, or he's still unable to detect this as long as it's used responsibly.

There's no real confirmation of there being an autoban system in place which detects your playstyle as being unusual but I'm going to assume there isn't. Also there doesn't seem to be an autoban system in place which is capable of detecting the functionality of this mod else I would be banned by now.

So I'll assume that bans are done manually and the administration doesn't have time to monitor thousands of users so they're likely only monitoring through replays in the top 40, and most likely only of which are very obvious or have been reported.

Some advice to avoid a ban:

Don't ever visit theaquila.net while the Osu! client is open.

Wouldn't recommend ever trying to rank #1 with cheats on, even if you do have a playcount of 100+ on that map. The legitimacy of your replay isn't always checked, someone may report your score out of spite even when you do play without cheats (I know of people who have been banned just for ranking first on a map without cheating - because their name isn't familiar for ranking first).

Personally my highest ranking was 2nd, I did get rank #1 on a new insane map once because I forgot that HD mod was on - my only 'oh shit' moment. In order to make it look more legitimate I played the same map with HD mod about 20 or so more times., luckily I wasn't #1 on that map for long. xD

Getting FC with either HD OR FL is more like than getting FC with both HD AND FL. Only use both on maps that are sure to be possible with both (and have been cleared previously by people using both). Also, never be the first on a map to rank high with FL, especially not insane maps (and ranking with FL on insane maps is pushing it).

Ensure that in your profile, your minimum playcount in the list of most played maps is 100+ or at least 50+. You're less likely to be reported because other users will be unable to assume that you got a good ranking in a minimal amount of plays. Generally, it's easy enough to rank with HD on most maps with just 10 to 20 plays, much more required for FL on harder maps.

I'd also recommend your account be at least 6 months old or else you may be reported for multi-account considering it's unlikely for someone to be capable of playing with mods in their first few months of playing. Additionally, I'd recommend having at least 4k PP before competing with top 20 ranks on harder maps.
[/quote]

There is no autoban system, It's [url=http://osu.ppy.sh/u/55]Zallius[/url] that bans you. How I know this? I was talking to a BAT on TeamSpeak, not going to say any names tho.

4667.subject: RE: This is my warning out to you guys!
4667.message:
I've found a pumper to use while Kev finds a solution. (Assuming you want to take the extra precaution.)

I've tested it myself and it works. If you get an error with .net framework you need to run this as an administrator. 

As far as I am aware this isn't backdoored, I scanned it and nothing all too suspicious showed up. 

Here's the download link: http://up.ht/WFp2Cc




How to use it:

1. Load up the aio.exe. 
2. Browse for the Exe file. Mine is located in a folder called google (I've disguised it as google chrome), so I go there and select the bot's EXE file. 
3. Use the file pumper to fake a certain file size. I have mine faked to match a browser's file size. (1 Megabyte)


That's about it. If you get an error it's because you didn't run it as an administrator.

You can also change the icon but as far as I am aware that does nothing. 

I hope this helps

4688.subject: What may be coming out to you guys soon.
4688.message:
[IMG]http://i.imgur.com/dmcZ5n0.png[/IMG]

With this, I will soon be working on osu!veiled, which I may make for a very small fee ($3 - $5 for lifetime), which will basically start any of our osu! cheats (or any program on your PC for that matter) in a way such that he see much info at all. All he can see is this:
[IMG]http://i.imgur.com/luY3hOo.png[/IMG]

So renaming the .exe and setting your Window title to "" will leave him with:
| nameofexe ()
And thats it.

This means that peppy cannot take an MD5, or gain any information as to what programs you have running on your computer, or where they are. So no need to place your cheats in C:\Program Files\iTunes or whatever, this will block it all.

Unless Windows changes the way the user account architecture is done, this can NEVER be patched. EVER.

[b]Expect release sometime shortly :3[/b]

4709.subject: osu!maniac - osu!mania bot [Current stage: Investigating]
4709.message:
I would like to announce that I am now looking into creating a basic osu!mania bot called osu!maniac. Due to the conversion algorithm being very complex and we haven't quite sussed it out yet from source.

I am going to be looking into now, osu!maniac, an osu!mania bot which will act like autoplay, it will still have some customizability like getting less percentage etc.

[b]Please note: This bot may NEVER come to pass, it all depends on how feasible this route is.[/b] One problem is that the autoplay on osu!mania only presses the non-holds for 1 frame, so the faster your PC, the less likely this will work (although forcing osu! to run at 60 FPS means that autoplay will hold the key for 16.6667 ms). In fact when I run it at unlimited, I cant even see the keys "lighting up".

[b][u]Progress Indicator[/u][/b]

4900.subject: [Last updated 3/5/2013] Issues/Suggestions for osu!catcher!
4900.message:
Under the assumption that osu!catcher will be updated at some point in time, and eventually released, I will post bugs/errors that I have found, as well as suggest features that would be nice to see added.

The goal of this thread is to make osu!catcher as good as it possibly can be. 

I cannot say for certain that the bugs/errors I find are universal. They may only apply to me. It would be useful if anyone else in the beta could post bugs/errors and help confirm any bugs that may exist.


Configuration:
[code]
WindowTitle *Google Chrome*		 
TimeToWaitAfterNote *15* 	
DashKey *z* 			
NormalDash *0.5* 		
SliderDash *0.50*		
HumanAccuracy *9*		
TeleportMove *0*		
[/code]


NormalDash and accuracy varies greatly from map to map. Maps that are jumpy or require many dashes it would be better to have a lower value on normaldash. I tend to keep accuracy above 8, as a lot of maps just look extremely unnatural, even at 8.

Also, teleportmove is extremely glitchy.  

----------------------------------------------------------------------

[size=large][b]Map Issues[/b][/size]

I've encountered a number of maps that either partially work, don't work at all, or they .osu doesn't load. 

I've experimented to figure out why exactly some of these maps don't work and I really can't say what causes it, I don't really know. I've deleted my songlist and reloaded it many times to try to get these maps to work properly but they just don't.


Map: Black Hole - Pluto
[url=http://osu.ppy.sh/s/45074]Map Link[/url]
The difficulties Challenge and Expert only partially work. 
I haven't tested the easier diffs.

Map: Beatdrop - Phase 1
[url=http://osu.ppy.sh/s/54511]Map Link[/url]
The difficulty SHD partially works, at about 2/3rds of the map the bot stops working. I haven't tested other difficulties.

Map: nano - no pain, no game
[url=http://osu.ppy.sh/s/60214]Map Link[/url]
The difficulty AngelHoney does not work at all. (most of the time it freezes the bot) I haven't tested other difficulties.

Map: Renard - Rainbow Dash Likes Girls
[url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/57255]Map Link[/url]
I've always had trouble with this map. At first it partially worked, now it doesn't work at all. 

I will update this with more maps that I find, I only decided to list a few. For the most part, maps work. Although, it seems as if newer ranked maps the bot has difficulty with them, as they either partially work or do not work at all. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------

[size=large][b]Dashing and Movement[/b][/size]
[i](Streams and Sliders)[/i]

I've been using osu!catcher since it's initial release and I've come across multiple ideas that I think would be good to be added, as well as issues I see in general with the bot.

For one, the bot looks unnatural on the majority of maps (some look fine). In comparison to replays from other players it stands out. I think a big part of this is the fact that the bot seems to spam dash. This is honestly extremely strange, being a CTB player myself, no one really does this to the extent that the bot does. 

A suggestion I would like to see is some sort of better method to detect when the bot needs to dash; and to eliminate the dash spam. I.E. the bot HOLDS dash to dash rather then spams it. I think this would help so much in making the bot look more legit.

Another big issues in my eyes is the unnatural slider and streams. 
The bot just looks very strange on maps that have streams and SOME sliders. For example, if you use the bot on these maps:

Map: Galdeira - Almagest
[url=http://osu.ppy.sh/s/41933]Map Link[/url]
This map just looks very strange. 


Map: TQBF - The Big Black
[url=https://osu.ppy.sh/b/131891]Map Link[/url]
For the most part this looks okay. Near the middle of the map, the sliders look pretty unnatural. 
When the fruits fall down next to each other like this:
O~O
O~O
O~O

These are the sliders that can cause problems


Map: xi - Ascension to Heaven
[url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/34348]Map Link[/url]
The streams are unnatural and strange.

Map: xi - Freedom Dive
[url=https://osu.ppy.sh/s/39804]Map Link[/url]
The streams are unnatural and strange. 50/50

These are just a few examples.

So, in other words, what I would like to suggest is a better method to detect when the bot should dash, and to simply have the bot HOLD dash rather than spam it. 

A better method to convert sliders and streams to make them look more natural in CTB.

----------------------------------------------------------------------

[size=large][b]Feature Suggestions[/b][/size]

The lack of hardrock being supported is an issue that's always been apparent. I don't quite understand why hardrock doesn't work, but it would certainly be a wonderful addition to osu!catcher. 

Another feature I would love to see implemented is retry support. Taiko and I assume relax have retry support, so something along those lines to be added to osu!catcher would be wonderful.

Another issue that has risen recently in the most recent osu!catcher update is the removal of the border on the sides. I don't really like this personally. It's strange. If possible I would like to see the borders be put back.


These are simply my ideas, incite and findings with the bot. I honestly think it is pretty damn decent as is, but I would like to see it exceed "good" and be the best out there. 

well that's all. if anyone else finds bugs/errors please post it! (I don't even know if anyone else is in the beta)

thanks

[code]DT/NC: Seems to not want to start the song, ends up stop loading during the initial wait period before  on certain songs.

HC: Control+H enabling HC mode for Osu!Relax seems to not stay active whenever selecting a song. Also while trying to start HC mode on Osu!Relax, doesn't let it work as well.


Loggin/Start up: Seems to have some massive lag, or wait for it to log in, check for updates, etc.

Osu!Relax GUI: The GUI is a great concept, however it seems a bit buggy, and not properly initialized. (Will add more information on this shortly)[/code]


About all I've encountered since updating. I don't know if anyone else has had these problems or not.

5128.message:
[b][size=large]Explanation of problems with Jumps(not hyperdash), combos, and timing [/size][/b]

I'm going to explain some other problems I've found while testing with the bot. 

----------------------------------------------------------------------


One issue I've partially covered is Jumps. For the most part, there isn't too much of a problem with jumps, the jumps the bot has trouble with are jumps that aren't hyperdashed, and this isn't always the case, some maps it can catch jumps that aren't hyperdashed, but others it cannot. 

I do not know fully why it can't, I figure it is probably something to do with how the bot keeps combo (because at 1MS wait time it STILL seems to fail some jumps.), though I cannot say for certain. 

One prime example of this is this map:

Map: Hatsune Miku - Homework Crisis (Diff: Let's Jump)
Link: http://osu.ppy.sh/b/108021&m=0

The bot cannot keep combo on this map due to the jumps. I've tried quite a few times to get it to FC but it can't. Sometimes it just outright fails the map.

This is just one example, this issue applies to other maps, generally not as bad though. Due to this problem with jumps, there are maps that the bot cannot FC, it will either miss one fruit or multiple due to the placement of the fruits. Example:

o = Fruits
- = "Space"


o 
-o
--o
---o
----o
------o 
-----------o
---o       
-------------o < bot misses this fruit (not hyperdashed)
-----o
-------o
---------o
----------o



o
-o
--o
---o
----o
-----o
--------o
----------------o
---o  
----------------o < Bot catches this fruit (hyperdashed)
---o
--------o 
---------o
----------o



Sorry if the example is dumb xD

This kind of covers the issue with timing as well, because I assume that the way the bot times jumps/comboing makes it impossible to catch these fruits. I can't say

I'll add more on the topic if necessary.

5170.subject: RE: Playcount Increaser - WhoCares?
5170.message:
You only need to play the first 10 seconds of a song in order for it to count as a valid play.

Add 5 seconds on for restarting the map, 1 play = 15 seconds.
240 plays an hour.

You only really need around 100 plays if you're trying to make attempts look legitimate.

5293.subject: Requesting Hacks?
5293.message:
If you have a suggestion or idea, or just want to request a hack be made, post in this section. 

They can be for anything, however, it's unlikely anything non-osu! related would be considered, as Kev puts most of his time into creating/updating hacks for osu!, but you may request hacks for other games. 


There have already been quite a few hack requests for osu!, so your osu! hack request is likely to already have been made or considered! List of current working osu! hacks can be found in "Program updates" section.

Same config for other mod qq

[code]WindowTitle *Bloc-note *		// This is the window title.
TimerOffset *-5*			// This is how offset the Timer will be.
TimeToWaitOnNote *0* 		// This is how long you want to be waiting on the note for Mouse Assist.
MouseMoveType *2* 		// 0 = Full Auto, 1 = Circle Auto, 2 = Mouse Assist
MouseAssistStrength *0.50* 	// This is how strong Mouse Assist will act on your cursor.
MouseAssistPower *3*  		// This is how it scales, a higher number will make assist work closer to the note. Range is 1-5
MouseAssistDistanceStop *15*	// This is a circular area around the center of the note where assist will not function.
UseRelaxBot *0* 		// This is set to hit key "x" you must change the key in the osu! options to "x"[/code]

5747.subject: Alternate issue
5747.message:
Hi,

is there a way (e.x. in the config) to change the pace of when the bot alternates? Say, it would alternate all the time or it would single tap until the pace of the circles at once gets too close to say, Cookiezi's single tapping speed or alike.

:heart:

5749.subject: RE: Alternate issue
5749.message: Just change 'StreamTime' in u config for increase alternate keys

5753.subject: RE: Alternate issue
5753.message:
StreamTime defines the minimum time (in ms) between two notes in which your secondary key will be pressed.

Eg. Setting the variable to 500 will cause your secondary key to only be pressed if the time between two notes is less than 500ms.

So if you want only one key pressed at all times, set it to something very small like 10.
If you want to alternate both keys at all times, set it to something very big like 10000.

5765.subject: Avoiding detection
5765.message:
This would probably only be a problem if someone gets #1 records often or is a high profile user who constantly gets a lot of attention. I'm pretty sure Kev is aware of this.
There's a Chinese osu! client that analyzes replays and spits out a visual line graph of the offsets of individual clicks in relation to the map. Using osu!Relax to play through a map and then analyzing that replay with this client allows you to see that it's REALLY obvious you're using a bot. Random offsets or not, comparing it to a legit replay with the same accuracy makes it strikingly clear.
AFAIK this lead to a lot of speculation of Tom69's recent records before his ban. (This probably was a conclusive evidence too)

My point being: Is this impossible to overcome?

5867.subject: [PLEASE READ] I would just like some reassurance
5867.message:
I am one step away from purchasing lifetime subscription of Timewarp. 

Other than it being down right now due to an update as Kev told me earlier, I would like to ask the subscribers to tell me what you have experienced so far regarding the following:

1)How much down time do you experience with updates?
2)Do you get banned easily using timewarp? [ofc not being a retard with it and FC freedom dive on DT]
3)Can you play with spectators and not be noticed hacking?
4)How has your experience been with Timewarp in particular so far?
5)Will I get access to osu!enlighten with the regular lifetime? [just to clarify]

Thank you very much for your responses in advance.

5868.subject: RE: [PLEASE READ] I would just like some reassurance
5868.message:
1) It depends, Kev is still a student and he sometimes can't focus on updating all of the cheats.
2) It all depends again, if you know how to make it look legit you shouldn't banned.
3) If there are spectators and you use timewarp, the spectating thing will buffer for them at the percentage of timewarp you are playing on. So there is anti-bancho, which disables spectating and still allows you to submit scores.
4) It is a great cheat! Just be careful with it, and it's a little time consuming.
5) Yes! You will get enlighten and dejavu. Dejavu changes your hardware ID so oyu can bypass bans.

I hope this helps you!
[hr]
Edit: I also have a couple of videos to show you how insane timewarp can look, ask me if you wanna see them.

6135.subject: RE: What I can do with 2 osu windows?
6135.message:
You don't need 2 clients for a makeshift Hidden/Flashlight hack.
You can just record your playthrough without HD/FL using whatever program and then play it in the background, while starting the playthrough again with HD/FL.

In order to see the recorded playthrough, you'll need any program which can force transparency on windows like Powermenu: http://www.abstractpath.com/powermenu/

Open powermenu, then right-click the title bar of osu and set the transparency to something like 60%.

Then you need to try to play the recording synced to you playing the map in the osu client, it may take some tries to sync it perfectly.

I used to do this before using Kev's HD/FL hack.

6141.subject: Suggestion for 'Avoiding detection'
6141.message:
In response to the "Avoiding detection" thread, I'd like to suggest adding an additional manual offset function a bit like the current behaviour of Spacebar.

Personally I use spacebar to simulate a bit of poor capability on streams, but it could also be used to create a bit of extra randomness in order to make the graphing look more legitimate. (Decrease the additional offset and press spacebar randomly throughout the song)

This would be a function which happens randomly and causes a slight additional offset to the current offset value.

The amount of offset would be limited to the max delay possible for hitting 300, and the occurrence of delayed hits would vary depending on delay time (the larger the additional offset, the less likely they are to occur - this'll cause a few times where a hit was delayed fairly longer than normal, removing the appearance of uniform delay that has a distinctive min/max delay).

I'm not too sure whether any of this would really help. Just trying to think of ways in which we can have random offsets that are not based entirely on a single random range.
Could also cause further unusual offset depending on patterns of notes. Eg. If there are a stream of just 2 notes, we can define that as a pattern and add specific additional random offset to them. So whenever a stream of 2 occurs, it'll remove more uniform delay.

We could also define a rule in which subsequent notes may not be in a set offset range from eachother, so each note will have a different offset range from the previous.
Eg. If the offset is 5 from a previous note, the current note cannot also have a range of 5, we must subtract/add a random additional offset for that offset of 5.. so current offset would become 7 if we add 2 (determined by a set random additional offset - and whether we add or subtract it is determined by whichever would cause the total delay to exceed the max offset), then for the next note we need to subtract/add for that offset of 7.

6248.message:
When you patch Hidden, check the mods screen to see if the score multiplier has gone up to 1.06 (whether Hidden is active or not).

If it's still at 1.00 even when Hidden is unselected, the patch didn't work correctly so you have to open Enlighten and patch Hidden again until it does show 1.06.
Usually takes no more than two tries.


By the way Kev, will it ever be possible to disable the patch?
So if I want to play without it, or want to watch a replay etc, I don't have to restart the Osu client.

6284.subject: bosu - osu! bot autoclicker - version 0.6.4
6284.message:
[color=#800000][size=large]I no longer support this project.
You can download source files (as attachment)
and continue bot developing.
Please, read this post:
http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=582&pid=6462#pid6462 [/size][/color]
[hr]

[img]http://s45.radikal.ru/i110/1305/3e/8b257835bf9b.png[/img]
[video=youtube]http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=-n0tSfe0U6g[/video]

[b]Features[/b]: autoclicks, automoves, autospin

[b]Issues[/b]: fullscreen only, poor old-style console interface, random bugs, settings in txt file, [color=#800080][size=x-large][b]HOLDS SLIDERS BUT DOES NOT MOVE THEM[/b][/size][/color], no integration with osu (but it works with any version), DT works badly

[color=#FF0000][size=x-large][b]Express video guide: http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=vZuPTe-O_SE (read annotations)[/b][/size][/color]


Hotkeys:
S = start/stop
QW = -+ delay (like gas and break pedals)
A = autospin (if you neen spinhack only. you can disable this feature in settings)

System Reqs:
WinXP+
VC Redist 2012

[size=large]New versions:[/size]
[hr]
[color=#FFDAB9][size=x-large]UNRELEASED -  [b]0.7[/b][/size][/color]
- Starting sliders code. But I'm tired, try to make it yourself.
- Source files uploaded
[hr]
[size=x-large][color=#800000]07 may 2013 -  [b]0.6.4[/b][/color][/size]
- Fixed freeze if path is incorrect. In this case you'll get invalid path message.
- Added spinhack hotkey:
  Did it because I had few requests to make just an "autospin hack"
  Press A for spin, Press A once again to stop it.
  it works without starting clicker (S hotkey).
  You can disable this feature in settings: check SPINHACKHOTKEY value.
  It's just a cursor spin without holding any keys.
[hr]
[size=x-large][color=#800000]06 may 2013 -  [b]0.6.3[/b][/color][/size]
- Autospin and Automove options in settings (now you can turn it off)
- Fixed some issues with "parsing..." freeze
[hr]
[size=x-large][color=#800000]06 may 2013 -  [b]0.6.2[/b][/color][/size]
- Changed setting name: OSU_RESOLUTION to OSU_OBJECTS_AREA
It was very ambigious, I gave it more accurate name.
- Added HR status, changed time mode status output
- Little adjustment of spinner and also made it slightly faster
[hr]
[size=x-large][color=#800000]05 may 2013 -  [b]0.6[/b][/color][/size]
- Added HR support - check settings
- Fixed spinner bug in all resolutions
- Successfully Tested in 1680x1050, 1280x800, 1024x600, 1024x768
- I think it should work with WinXP (UPD: confirmed, it works!)
- Fixed black screen bug
- DT works much better (but still sloppy)
- Fixed mouse buttons problem (no longer need to disable this in osu options)
- Removed dealybytime option, it was useless, use delaybycode
- Fixed "0108 style" movement (many circles = one coords pair):
[img]http://s018.radikal.ru/i505/1305/7c/5f5f6b565977.jpg[/img]
[hr]

DOWNLOAD:
http://rghost.ru/45818660
http://ge.tt/3DzSRxf/v/0?c
or as attachment file.

VirusTotal:
https://www.virustotal.com/ru/file/099f7ad3ef9f9383e7fef9a0f85fda2b3690aa1f51588ed1abc3eeec767d1293/analysis/1367888403/

[color=#FF0000][size=x-large]English Guide/Readme:[/size][/color]
[spoiler]
1) unpack zip
2) open bosu.txt (read README part)
3) set your resolution
4) paste full map path
5) start exe, if everything is fine you'll get few beeps and instructions with current settings.

Fullscreen only.
S - start/stop
Q and W =    minus and plus delay GLOBALDELAYSTEP [ms] * each keypress   -   [gas and break pedals :3 ]
Example: you see your bot is late - press q few times. Now bot substract from each click time = GLOBALDELAYSTEP * amount of times q pressed. Then, when bot gets good timing, press w key until single audiobeep, now you have 0 globaldelay. If it's far ahead in clicking - use W first, then Q until beep. 
DELAYBYCODE [ms] in DBCN [clicks]  -- use it to compensate process delays.
!!! Try to find proper values for you system. Try first in range from 1:1 to 1:15.
!!! You will have less problems with synchro and QW pressing with right values.
OSU_OBJECTS_AREA - use only when resolution option works incorrectly
MODE - 1 normal, 2 dt, 3 ht (DTHT buggy)
STARTOBJECT - you can start from any point (N hitobject) of map you want
HR - 0  no, 1  yes
Automove - 0 no, 1 yes
Autospin - 0 no, 1 yes
[/spoiler]

6462.subject: RE: osu! bot autoclicker [free] - version 0.6.4
6462.message:
Bad/Good news guys

Bad news:
I started to code sliders and suddenly I realized that I'm kinda bored with this project. My enthusiasm is over. 
Sliders' algorithm is pretty much easy but it requires a lot of time to write it down, testing, try-and-erros, routine works, timing adjustment etc...

And since it was fun-project (and I got fun by coding this, topranking hardest maps and watching people fighting each other in gamechat and discussing it) but now it's not fun for me anymore. I achived what I wanted to achive. Now I want to do something else.

Maybe I'll come back later to finish it, but now I'm done with it.

Good news:
Source files uploaded (check 1st post).
Latest is 0.7, but you can check previous versions aswell to understand my code.
[size=large][b]Please excuse me for low quality of my code - I'm not even a university student yet :sleepy:
I'm just studying it by myself and I hadn't plans to release it in the beginning.[/b][/size]

You can complete sliders by yourslef.
If you going to try [b]here is my suggestions:[/b]
1) Learn osu map files.
2) Learn my code (it's not that hard)
I started slidergetcoors() function which one now successfully takes coords and reverse int from map. You should finish rest.

3) !!! visit these links:

http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=150
read about TimingPoints and Sliders.
---
http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/B%C3%A9zier_curve
---
Best simple tutorial for curves:
http://www.codeproject.com/Articles/25237/Bezier-Curves-Made-Simple
It's in C#. But I encourage you to undestand not code and formulas in this article,
but geometric principle of this solutions. When you understand - it's quite obvious
how to code it down in c++ in "easy" way. 

4) Remember:
2 points = straight line
3 points = in most cases it's a part of triangle circumcircle
more than 3 points = use your Bezier Curve algorithm

Don't forget about reverse int in slider strings and timing points.

P.S. I used mingw compiler.


Well, this is it :angel:

6555.message:
[quote='boko' pid='6135' dateline='1367172183']
You don't need 2 clients for a makeshift Hidden/Flashlight hack.
You can just record your playthrough without HD/FL using whatever program and then play it in the background, while starting the playthrough again with HD/FL.

In order to see the recorded playthrough, you'll need any program which can force transparency on windows like Powermenu: http://www.abstractpath.com/powermenu/

Open powermenu, then right-click the title bar of osu and set the transparency to something like 60%.

Then you need to try to play the recording synced to you playing the map in the osu client, it may take some tries to sync it perfectly.

I used to do this before using Kev's HD/FL hack.
[/quote]
Yes, we can create thread in osu! Tutorials.

6566.message:
When I play with "UseRelaxBot" on, it doesn't hit a lot of notes. Basically, auto moves to the object, but it doesn't click. If it does it usually is a 50.

Config:
[spoiler]
WindowTitle *hai - Notepad*		// This is the window title.
TimerOffset *-10*			// This is how offset the Timer will be.
TimeToWaitOnNote *20* 		// This is how long you want to be waiting on the note for Mouse Assist.
MouseMoveType *0* 		// 0 = Full Auto, 1 = Circle Auto, 2 = Mouse Assist
MouseAssistStrength *0.40* 	// This is how strong Mouse Assist will act on your cursor.
MouseAssistPower *3*  		// This is how it scales, a higher number will make assist work closer to the note. Range is 1-5
MouseAssistDistanceStop *20* 	// This is a circular area around the center of the note where assist will not function.
UseRelaxBot *1* 		// This is set to hit key "x" you must change the key in the osu! options to "x"
[/spoiler]

6763.subject: RE: Suggestion for 'Avoiding detection'
6763.message:
It doesn't need to detect a 'method' for random offset.
It would just need to record the exact hit time of each note - of which it already does because an average delay range is calculated (hover over your accuracy when you finish a map).

I don't think the osu client currently does anything in relation to the max/min delay times and it doesn't do anything with correlation of those times (like determining whether the delay is linear or sporadic depending on how often a specific range of delay occurs)

It really wouldn't be all that difficult to detect, but its not an absolute method of detecting cheaters.

I haven't used the graph thing but I'm assuming all it does is put data that is already available into a more user friendly format.

6809.subject: osu!enlighten bug
6809.message:
Someone has disabled my ability to post in 'Osu! tutorials' (I get a permission error.. nobody told me I was barred from it but whatever), so I guess I'll put this here.

There are 2 bugs with Enlighten hack:
#1: If you do not ensure that the score multiplier stays active after attempting to patch and it doesn't turn out to be patched, your score will not rank with the difference of the multiplier even though you will be ranked with Hidden enabled.

This first one is a known issue, just making people aware. If someone sees your score with HD mod but you're ranked around people without mods, you risk being reported.

#2: When playing with HR enabled, it's suppose to make spinners more difficult so you get less score with it enabled, but with englighten active (tested with only HD, not HR/FL patch), you're able to get a greater score on spinners as if you had HR disabled.
This might just be a visual bug, because when restarting the client and checking the replay, it shows you getting regular HR spinner scores. I'm not too sure if this has any effect on spin speed (I got 12k during play, replay showed it as 9k at about 380 speed), or if the score is added even though the replay shows differently

6810.subject: RE: osu!enlighten bug
6810.message: I can confirm these issues, albeit the first one rather rare, it's actually happened to me and one of my scores was ranked #3 instead of #1 due to it.

Just ensure the multiplier is correct by disabling and re-enabling Hidden on the mods screen to see if it changes.. if it does then it isn't properly patched and requires re-patching by restarting enlighten.. when it is patched, it shouldn't decrease from +0.06 multiplier even when disabled.

6832.subject: RE: osu!Enlighten, free for subscribers (FL/HD/HR hack.)
6832.message:
I just had a problem... 
-I had ranked a map with no hacks that gave me pp.
-Today i passed that score (ranked it above it) and it didn't gave me pp, instead, it removed me all the pp i gained before with that map (using FL hack)

any idea why?

6833.subject: RE: osu!Enlighten, free for subscribers (FL/HD/HR hack.)
6833.message:
[quote='CaptainFalcon' pid='6832' dateline='1369275450']
I just had a problem... 
-I had ranked a map with no hacks that gave me pp.
-Today i passed that score (ranked it above it) and it didn't gave me pp, instead, it removed me all the pp i gained before with that map (using FL hack)

any idea why?
[/quote]

I'm fairly sure this is just an issue with how the display of PP updates on the client side.
PP doesn't visually update instantly in the client, I think it's cached until you gain PP from a map (takes load off the server because it doesn't have to send as many updates).
It's the same as checking maps that you previously ranked on, you have to manually refresh them (by clicking global ranking) to refresh the rankings to see where you're currently ranked.

During the period of which you haven't gained any PP, you will still be losing PP from other maps that other people are out-ranking you on, and that sometimes only gets deducted from the visual representation on your client after you had gained PP and considering the amount lost is more than you gained, it seems as if you just lost PP from doing good on a map when in fact your PP was lower than you assumed it to be before ranking on that map.

To put it short:
-PP gain updates instantly when your ranking on a map meets criteria for PP.
-PP loss only updates on a set interval or when you gain PP.
-If you lose 50 PP since the last update and gain 40 PP from the map you just ranked, it will show as a loss of 10 PP overall.

6840.subject: [Tip] Link Dejavu with Osu! for efficiency.
6840.message:
Hi guys.

I have thought about people forgetting to start dejavu by mistake and then ban so I decided it would be a good idea to share a simple tip to start both as if they are one application.

We start by locating our osu file.
[code]C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!\osu!.exe[/code]
That is the default directory.

Then our osu!dejavu file.
[code]C:\Users\dil\Documents\torrents\basic\reset.exe[/code]
This is just where mine is located, obviously yours will be different.

We next open up notepad and write the following:

[code]@echo off
rem osu
cd "C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!
start osu!.exe
rem dejavu
cd C:\Users\dil\Documents\torrents\basic
start reset.exe
exit
[/code]

Next we will want to save this file like so:
[img]http://puu.sh/2ZA7U.png[/img]

Save it to your desktop for easy access if you like...That's where I keep mine.
[img]http://puu.sh/2ZAdA.png[/img]



[Optional update to convert to .exe and add icon]

Download this program: [url=http://sourceforge.net/projects/bat2exe/files/latest/download?source=dlp]Batch to EXE converter[/url]

Make a folder on your desktop, in this case I named it [size=large]what[/size]

Copy your batch file and an icon file of your choice into that folder.

Start the Bat to EXE converter you downloaded from that link.

Enter the path of your batch file eg : [code]c:users\dil\desktop\what[/code]

Press enter and it will build the exe for you...

Look inside the folder that you told the program to search for the bat and ico file to find your exe.

Result:
[img]http://puu.sh/2ZByg.png[/img]

DOMO-SU! :3

Opposite to my username, please:
[img]http://i.imgur.com/lEty8Y5.png[/img]

6890.subject: RE: [Tip] Link Dejavu with Osu! for efficiency.
6890.message:
Just a little note for those who use multiple drives, you have to add the drive letter on it's own line before cd or it won't change directory properly.

Here's an example:
[code]@echo off
D:
cd "D:\Program Files (x86)\osu!"
start osu!.exe
E:
cd E:\Users\dil\Documents\torrents\basic
start reset.exe
exit[/code]

Oh! Maybe Kev could make dejavu work automatically(Patch and then close) if you were to run the program with the command:
start reset.exe -auto
or something of that nature. Obviously only if the LL file is already there and valid and what not.

I think I'll go legit again, I used Relax to clear some maps I had a hard time with.

7168.subject: RE: osu!veiled - Hide your programs from detection
7168.message:
Tutorial on how to stay as safe as possible:

1. Open osu!veiled
2. Select Hack.exe (svchost as name is good)
3. Click Open programm in veiled-mode
4. Click OK on the Successful popup
5. Close osu!veiled
6. Start Taskmanager
7. Kill PSEXESVC.exe
8. Start osu!

Just do the steps above and you're good to go

Don't forget to do the Steps in the first post regarding the Data folder and the renaming.


Cheers

7220.subject: RE: HD/FL Method
7220.message:
I can't remember what programs Niko used and I've never tried his method so not too sure on some details.

But basically you need a program which can run an application in a sandbox.
Like this: http://www.sandboxie.com/ (so you can run multiple instances of Osu!)

Then you run Osu! as you normally do + another instance of Osu! in the sandbox and align the windows correctly so your cursor positions are the same in both windows.

Recently, Osu! was patched to force 'always on top' and 100% opacity when a map is playing, so it's not possible to have the sandbox above the original client so you need to be logged into your account on the sandbox and be as a guest in the original.

I'm not sure if Sandboxie provides this functionality itself but you need some program/method to copy key presses to multiple windows. You'll be playing normally in the original client (as guest, with no mods), and the Sandboxie osu! will copy your cursor movements/key presses from the original client (logged in, with mods).

I know that you can do this with AutoHotKey by creating a script similar to:
WinGet, id, list, osu!

z::
KeyWait, z, D
ControlSend,, {z}, ahk_id %id1%
ControlSend,, {z}, ahk_id %id2%
Return

x::
KeyWait, x, D
ControlSend,, {x}, ahk_id %id1%
ControlSend,, {x}, ahk_id %id2%
Return

The above assumes that osu! is the process title of the sandboxie client though, and I'm not sure whether that is the case. (I've never used sandboxie)
You can probably find a better program for such a task on google.

You might be able to change the above code to check for the sandboxie client as well, but I haven't tried.


It's a prett longwinded method, and will probably not work too well because of the random delay (you'll have to manually stop both clients at the same time in the map then enable whatever you're using to copy keystrokes then unpause both at the same time).
Better to just buy one of the programs to get enlighten.

7271.subject: RE: 'Relax' Programming Example
7271.message:
Yeah, I'm not sure if I made myself clear enough.

The program that I've offered is not complete, it does work.. but it's not able to hit notes at correct times, there's also a few smaller issues (detecting pause is iffy etc).

If you want to use it, you have to make some changes in order to get it to work.
It's a programming learning experience, I'm not giving away a fully functional hack out of the box, you have to work for it. Kev wouldn't want me to give away a free fully functional hack, so this is the only way you're getting a free one.

There isn't very much you have to add to it to get it to work and I did list some clues.
The main problem is the timing method used. You need to understand that the minimum timing of a timer object is something like 50ms, so it's not fast enough to keep up with a song that requires every millisecond.

It's not too difficult, and the better timing method isn't all that complicated, it's one of the basic things you learn about programming.

The complicated part is adding slider support, I won't provide any help for that.

7294.subject: RE: Timewarp + Relax
7294.message:
My antivirus+firewall are disabled.

Config files: 
Timewarp
WindowTitle *-*			// This is the title you want the program to go by.
PercentChange *5.0* 			// This is how much you will change the song percentage per key press.
DecreaseSpeed *u*			// Key you will press to decrease the song speed.
IncreaseSpeed *i*				// Key you will use to increase the song speed.
DoubleTimeToggle *t*			// Key you will use to toggle DoubleTime flag.
SpinnerSpeed *100.00*			// This allows you to spin at a slightly slower song speed, you will be spin hacking such that no one will notice.

Relax:
WindowTitle *-*
TimerOffset *1*             	// This has become rather accurate, but setting it high will make it easier to play.
RandomOffsets *22*	 	// This works in either way, so 15ms will be a 30ms window!
SecondaryOffsets *16*		// This number should be an EVEN number, and should be between 14-18 for the best legit output.
KeyPattern *0* 			// 0 = KeyPresses, 1 = Mouse Clicks, 2 = Key/Mouse
MainKeyOne *z*			// This is the key you hit the most.
MainKeyTwo *x*			// This is the key you use to stream with.
NormalKeyDownDuration *60*
StreamKeyDownDuration *40*
StreamTime *140*		// This is the duration between notes that you will alternate keys.

7409.subject: osu!veiled - mklink "Data" folder
7409.message:
Here's a pretty nice way to link your 'Data' folder from your osu! hacks straight to system32 or SysWOW64 so there is only one 'Data' folder on your computer and any changes made to the original one will be accessed by the hacks when using osu!veiled.

First off it is worth noting that this will only really work for you if all of your osu! hacks are in one directory and they all share a 'Data' folder(It is possible to repeat this for multiple different directories but "ain't nobody got time fo dat"). For this example this directory will be "[color=#FF0000]C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!hacks[/color]". If this isn't the case for you feel free to either move your hacks to one place and make them share a data folder or just read through this anyway and repeat the steps for each different folder.

Also, please delete any 'Data' folders you already have in either system32 or SysWOW64 before continuing.

Once that is all set up it's time to open up cmd and admin. To do this go to your start menu and type "cmd". Right click the first result and press "run as administrator".

This is what you need to enter for 32-bit operating systems:
[code]mklink /j "C:\Windows\System32\Data" "C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!hacks\Data"

And then press enter...[/code]

This is what you need to enter for 64-bit operating systems:
[code]mklink /j "C:\Windows\SysWOW64\Data" "C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!hacks\Data"

And then press enter...[/code]

If this didn't work for remember to open cmd as admin and also remember that your actual 'Data' directory should be entered rather than "[color=#FF0000]C:\Program Files (x86)\osu!hacks\Data[/color]" but the "C:\Windows\SysWOW64\Data" and "C:\Windows\System32\Data" should remain as they are because it is the same for all Windows pc's... I think...

7410.subject: RE: osu!veiled - Hide your programs from detection
7410.message:
[quote='Smurfz' pid='7168' dateline='1370509677']
Tutorial on how to stay as safe as possible:

1. Open osu!veiled
2. Select Hack.exe (svchost as name is good)
3. Click Open programm in veiled-mode
4. Click OK on the Successful popup
5. Close osu!veiled
6. Start Taskmanager
7. Kill PSEXESVC.exe
8. Start osu!

Just do the steps above and you're good to go

Don't forget to do the Steps in the first post regarding the Data folder and the renaming.

7569.subject: Legit Movement Config Explained
7569.message:
With the release of the legit movement I have made, there are still many things I have to implement and rework to make them much better and more customizable.


This is what a default config looks like (the config it is located at "Data\Configs\Legit.cfg"):
[code]SliderCutOff
45.0
CircleScale
0.4
PercentTimeToMove
0.95
SpinClockWise
0
SpinnerAngle
0.75
MaxSpinnerDiameter
25.0
MinSpinnerDiameter
17.0
SpinnerEaseOutTime
300.0
MovePercentiles
0.08
0.20
0.72
0.95
1.00
PercentileMaxSpeed
1.00
3.25
6.00
3.00
1.00
PercentileDivisionsLow
3.0
3.0
1.45
1.5
5.0
PercentileDivisionsHigh
7.0
5.0
2.0
2.5
8.0[/code]

Now to break everything down so that users can understand this and begin to customize things to their liking...

[b]SliderCutOff[/b]
This value is scaled to match the window size and is used to determine how far away a movement in a slider must be prior to moving to the next coordinate.  A larger value will prevent the movement from moving to every single point on a slider when there happens to be a large amount of points in the same spot.

[b]CircleScale[/b]
This value specifies how far from the center of a note the mouse will aim.  If this is set to 0.90 or 1.00 it will likely only aim at the edge of the notes, and if this was set to 0.00 it would attempt to be at the center of the note all the time.  (I didn't know what to name the variable.)

[b]PercentTimeToMove[/b]
This value specifies what percentage of the movement note to note should be actual move times.  When set to 0.95, the mouse will move to the note and then proceed to sleep 5% of the time that it was not moving.  Decrease this value to make the mouse sit on a note longer and make the movement faster between notes.

[b]SpinClockWise[/b]
This value is only 1 and 0, if set to 1 it will spin clockwise, if set to 0 it will spin counter-clockwise.

[b]SpinnerAngle[/b]
This controls which way the spin oval will appear.  Hard to explain but -0.75 will make it spin left-top to bottom-right, 0.75 will spin right-top to bottom-left.

[b]MaxSpinnerDiameter[/b]
This value controls how large the diameter of the spin will be.  It will vary between +2 and -6 of the value specified (these values will be customizable soon.)

[b]MinSpinnerDiameter[/b]
This value controls how small the diameter of the spin will be.  It will vary between +2 and -6 of the value specified (these values will be customizable soon.)

[b]SpinnerEaseOutTime[/b]
This value is how many milliseconds the spinner will continue to spin while slowing down after a spinner.  If there is a note within the window it should stop spinning and move to the note.

[b]MovePercentiles[/b]
These values are related to the next variables.  The percentiles are broken up into 5 different groups, based on the default config the first MovePercentile is 0.08 (8%) of the mouse movement and will attempt to stay around a movement of 1.0 (PercentileMaxSpeed) pixels per two milliseconds, the PercentileDivisionsLow of 3.0 will cause the movement to increase slower when it is below the PercentileMaxSpeed since the PercentileDivisionsHigh is 7.0 and will cause the movement to decrease faster when it is above 1.0 (PercentileMaxSpeed).

[b]PercentileMaxSpeed[/b]
These values are the max amount of pixels per two milliseconds that the mouse will move in each percentile.

[b]PercentileDivisionsLow/PercentileDivisionsHigh[/b]
These values are kind of explained in MovePercentiles, although adjusting these values by too much will cause some issues and might cause the program to crash.  I don't feel like changing these values will cause any huge noticeable movement differences, but I still have included them for users who feel like they want to change stuff.


[i]Any questions can be posted in here, but please be sure to read this thread prior to asking a question to make sure your question has not already been asked and answered![/i]

7613.subject: HOW NOT TO GET BANNED - PLEASE READ NEW USERS
7613.message:
[size=large][color=#FFFFFF][b]UPDATED 22/09/2013[/b][/color][/size]

[color=#98FB98][b]Remember, you are in full control to whether or not you get banned. You can hack for your whole osu! career and not get banned but make one silly mistake, and that's all it takes. These are guidelines I follow, and I haven't been banned since.[/b][/color]

Just to be safe: [b][color=#FFFFFF]AFTER EVERY osu! UPDATE, TRY TO WAIT [u]1-2 days[/u] BEFORE USING HACKS. THERE MAY BE DETECTION UPDATES UNNOTICED BY KEV [/color] 
[/b]
First of all, if you feel unsafe with hacks, use a VPN or proxy to hide your IP address, to avoid getting IP banned. You should also use a separate account if you're scared of your main account getting banned.

[size=medium][b][color=#FF0000]Strict Guidelines[/color][/b][/size]
These rules are what you should follow to avoid being detected by peppy.

Here's a VPN thread: http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=675
And use google to find how to use proxies :D

[size=large][b][color=#FF0000]osu!veiled is no longer an effective method to avoid detection. Read this thread for instructions how how to stay undetected:[/color][/b][/size] http://www.theaquila.net/showthread.php?tid=793

1.) [b]ALWAYS[/b] start osu! logged off, so that you can run all the programs/bots offline, just to be safe.

[size=medium][b]Self - Control Guidelines[/b][/size]
If you do use hacks, these rules are what you should follow to avoid getting flagged. These rules help you immensely to not getting banned if you have followed the strict guidelines correctly.

1.) TRY NOT TO get high ranks on too many songs in one day (4+)

2.) Don't hack everyday. Take days off with your hacks and play legitimate. 

3.) Avoid rank 1's as much as possible unless you have a very high play count on the songs (150+).

4.) Trying to beat Cookiezi's #1 ranks will just attract a lot of attention towards yourself, I highly recommend that you don't unless your are ready to be investigated.

[u][b]FLASHLIGHT GUIDELINES[/b][/u]

1.) Only use flashlight on songs where other people have used them for top 50's. 

2.) At breaks or pauses on songs, be sure you remember to put your cursor over/near the upcoming hit circle.

3.) Try as hard as you can to reach the hitcircles with your cursor before the actually appear on short pauses to make it look like you have memorized the map, this may take a good # of plays.

4.) Have a decent play count before using FL. A safe number is 50+ on Hard/Insanes. Easy/Normal difficulties take less play count.

5.) The most important: MAKE IT LOOK LIKE YOU"RE ACTUALLY USING FL MOD while using the hack. Try completing songs offline and look at your own replay and confirm that it looks legit before getting top 50's on a song online.

Update: 30/10/2013

7770.subject: Good way of getting to high ranking safely?
7770.message: Well I have been experimenting with osu! hacks including relax and enlighten. I actually have gotten to top 10 ranking in US 4 times consecutively with this method before getting banned and I wanted to know if it is a bad idea or not. So what I basically do is I play all "hard" difficulty songs and get to top 10 rankings in all of them (Hd, Dt). Perhaps I got impatient and ranked up too fast, I got banned for all of them. Now, if we say that we do this on long term, would this be a good idea to get to high ranking pretty safely?

7771.subject: RE: Good way of getting to high ranking safely?
7771.message: Start by just accumulating playcount. Then after a while, try to get good ranks on the maps that you have high playcounts on. Or you could grind on easy-normal maps for 3-4 months. Then move on to hard, then insane.

7797.subject: How to Dump EHsvc.dll Themida (HackShield Games)
7797.message:
You need :

[color=#32CD32]Hackshield Folder 
Ehsvc.dll
OllyDBG
Plugin StrongOD
Plugin PE Dumper
[/color]

[color=#FF0000]Introduction:

EHsvc.dll is the main dll of Hackshield , to create an emulator need to know their roles and fuctions , but the problem is Themida Protection.
[/color]

Lets Dump :

[size=large]1: Press ALT + O and set Debugging Option so:[/size]
[SPOILER][img]http://s2.postimg.org/5j2v8ioqh/hs1.png[/img][/SPOILER]
[size=large]2: Open StrongOD and set it so Plugin > StrongOD[/size]
[SPOILER][img]http://s2.postimg.org/vdcnyaoqh/hs2.png[/img][/SPOILER]
[size=large]3: Open Ehsvc.dll in Ollydbg[/size]
[size=large]4: Press CTRL + G > GetProcessHeap > Accept
5: Search On RETN and set a Break Point on HW:[/size]
[SPOILER][img]http://s2.postimg.org/f7gbbnjjs/hs3.jpg[/img][/SPOILER]
[size=large]6: Press F9 
7: RightClick > Analysis > Analysis Code.
8: RightClick > Make Dump of The Process > Select Ehsvc.dll and press Dump[/size]
[SPOILER][img]http://s2.postimg.org/gjy0djgzd/hs4.png[/img][/SPOILER]
[size=large]9: Save > DLL file.[/size]

now be read completely:
[SPOILER][img]http://s2.postimg.org/hdf7jwce0/hs5.jpg[/img][/SPOILER]


[color=#32CD32]Next tutorial:
How to Emulate hackshield (Bypass)[/color]

7937.subject: Replay Stealing Based Mania Bot?
7937.message:
What would the community think about a mania bot that would basically take a saved replay file (produced by osu!topus!) and then use that to detect the notes in the song on how to play.

A few features that would be included:

Blowing through replay watching in less than 2-3 seconds per 5 minutes of a song.  
Human like offsets and key presses.
Basically anything that relax has for security features to ensure detection is minimal.


This would end up being a joined effort from Cookiezi and I to hopefully produce this as fast and efficiently as possible.


Progress:
[list]
