8131.subject: osu!Maniac Setup and Usage Guide.
8131.message:
Prior to even loading the program you should do these steps to ensure that all will work well:
[list=1]
[*] Extract the .rar file you have downloaded, ensure you keep the file structure.
[*] Browse to your osu! folder and copy the "[b]osu.dll[/b]" ([u]not the "osu!.dll"[/u]) and place the osu.dll in the Data folder of Maniac.
[*] Open osu!, go to the Options and click on the Input tab.  By default the "Osu!mania layout" is set to Symmetrical, if you have not already changed this, set it to "Left to Right."
[*] If you wish to disable the rainbow GUI, browse to the "Data\Configs\ManiacRainbow.cfg" and open the file with Notepad.  Replace the "1" with a "0" and save/close the file.
[/list]

The data folder should look like this:
[img]http://www.theaquila.net/Announcements/osu!Maniac/Images/folder.png[/img]


[u][b]osu!Maniac Config Explained[/b][/u]:
(After logging into Maniac you may click on the Edit Config button at any time.)
[list]
[*][b]Key Down Time[/b]: This is how long you will hold a single tap key down for.  It is best to keep this around 20-30 so that there are no issues.
[*][b]Timer Offset[/b]: Same as every other bot, just a way to adjust the timer for hitting notes.  Adjust this if you seem to be hitting too early or too late on average.
[*][b]Random Offsets[/b]: This is a minor value to assist in creating legit offsets.  I advise keeping it the same as Secondary Offsets.
[*][b]Secondary Offsets[/b]: This is the value that creates the legit timing.  If you only want rainbow 300s, it is best to keep this around 8.  Using a value around 30 simulates what some of the best Mania players can do.
[*][b](Rainbow 300s, Normal 300s, 200s, 100s, 50s)[/b]: These values are percentages, all of these values MUST add up to 100.0.  You can change these to have osu!Maniac offset notes throughout the song so you score differently.  It is strongly advised to keep the Rainbow 300s setting higher than 85.0.
[/list]





[u][b]How to use osu!Maniac[/b][/u]:
[list=1]
[*]Locate the song you would like it to play.
[*]Apply "Auto" mod on and start the song so that you will watch osu! create a replay of the song.  Maniac will speed through this replay, sometimes even skipping the whole replay.
[*]Once at the score screen hit F2 to save the replay, osu!Maniac should detect this and will then extract and store the replay for later use.
[*]You can now load up that song without Auto mod and it will play the song.  (osu!Maniac's config is loaded at the start of the song.)
[/list]


[u][b]How to use Mass Replay[/b][/u]:
[list=1]
[*]Begin at the song select menu with Mania mode.
[*]Apply Auto mod on.
[*]Click on the button.
[*]Maniac will now go down the list of songs, saving replays and extracting them for you.
[*]Press F4 to stop this mode.
[/list]

8245.subject: New method to hiding programs
8245.message:
This should be much safer than veiled methods ever were...  Sorry about that guys :x

This is for 32bit people:
[spoiler]
People on 32bit have it pretty easy, there is a tool out there called Hide Toolz v2.2 ([url=http://www.mediafire.com/download/lntm3vzkhe2/Hide]Link Here[/url].)  Use that program to right click programs in the list and hide them.
[/spoiler]

This is for 64bit people:
[spoiler]
Credits for the programs go to Fyyre, the tools has has for hiding programs are extremely nice.  Pretty simple also.

First you will need to disable PatchGuard ([url=http://fyyre.ivory-tower.de/projects/no_pg_ds_v3.rar]Using this[/url] [[url=http://fyyre.ivory-tower.de/projects/disable_pg_win8.rar]This if you're Win 8[/url] I don't have a Win 8 system so I can't offer support, this one takes more knowledge than average people.].)  There is a readme.txt file in the .rar folder, please note you have to [b]disable User Account Control[/b] prior to starting to ensure this works.  You will want to then select "PatchGuard Disabled v3" on boot.

After having done so, you will need [url=http://fyyre.ivory-tower.de/projects/hidecon.rar]this program[/url].  Hidecon works entirely off command prompt.  Once you extract hidecon, you will want to open a command prompt in the same directory.  On Win Vista/7 you and SHIFT+Right Click and you will see "Open command window here."

[img]http://puu.sh/496Cv/54f9ac2278.png[/img]

The first thing you will want to type in the command prompt is: "hidecon -ld"
[img]http://puu.sh/496X4/7d2f30e9ea.png[/img]
This will load up the driver so you can then hide processes.  Now type "hidecon -l" to get a list of the processes and process ID's.  Note down the ProcessID numbers that you wish to hide!

For every processID that you want to hide you must type "hidecon -ph xxxx" (Replacing the x's with the number of the process.  You can then choose to close the cmd window, or you could even hide that to be lazy and keep it open.

Ex:
[img]http://puu.sh/496Vh/f6abfdfaa1.png[/img]
[/spoiler]

[u]Things to remember (This list will grow.)[/u]
[list=1]
[*][b]Always unhide your programs prior to exiting them![/b]
[/list]

Note: Blue Screens of Death seem to be common around this type of hiding... Feel free to contribute things that may cause a Blue Screen so that other users may prevent this from occurring to them!

8642.subject: RE: Osu enlighten problem
8642.message: This Error is in most cases tagged as a problem with some missing runtime files, what might be true sometimes, but the error often goes really deep into registry issues that are not fixed that easily. It might aswell be a harddrive error, what also is not fixed within 5 minutes. You can check if it is a runtime error or a registry error by simply trying to change something in your startup. If it's a registry error you won't be able to change something there. For me, only a Windows reinstall fixed this problem! :(

8664.subject: [Tip] Get raw mouse input in Win7/8!
8664.message:
Hey guys :)

Been a while since I posted anything here...
Well, as I am sure all of you have noticed, not often do games include the "RAW INPUT" mouse setting anymore like Counterstrike. 

With Windows 7 and 8 there is no true way built in feature to disable all of the mouse acceleration even if you turn pointer precision off in the control panel.

Enough with the chatter though, I recently came across this:
[url=http://donewmouseaccel.blogspot.com/2010/03/markc-windows-7-mouse-acceleration-fix.html]MarkC Win7/8 mouse acceleration fix[/url].
The download link to the zip as well as instructions and explanations are on that linked site.

Basically there are a bunch of .reg files in the zip folder you get, and you choose the one which is your dpi setting in windows [default is on 100% for Win7]. You have to set your mouse speed to the middle in windows and turn off pointer precision for the fix to work.

After applying the .reg file just reboot your pc and you will have raw mouse input in your Windows 7/8 PC :P

Enjoy the accurate jumps.

8922.message:
Hidden and all enlighten functions are perfectly fine...If you are using hidecon, [and/or] you are starting your bot before you log in to your account then I suggest you do this:

1.Open osu! [Guest offline mode]
2.Open hack
3.Hide hack with hidecon
4.Go into your map list and patch hidden with enli
5.Check to see the score is 0.6
6.If not 0.6 patch again.
7.Now login to your osu account and you will have your hidden patched while logged in.

It seems there is an issue regarding starting up enli while you are in guest user mode,  then logging in, and patching once you are logged in to your osu account. I am sure you can see now this is simple logic and very easy to accomplish.

9078.subject: Stream with your iPhone
9078.message:
Hello AQN.

I would like to share a fun and handy trick with you. Some of you may have already figured this out. If you have, good for you! If you haven't, I am sure you will have fun with this.

As you can see by the title of this thread, this is for iPhone users.

Things you will need: Joypad Legacy, Joypad connect for PC.
Both can be found [url=http://getjoypad.com/legacy/]here.[/url]
Of course the iPhone app can also be found by searching Joypad Legacy in the Appstore.

Once you have installed the app on your iPhone and downloaded Joypad connect for PC, open up the app and select the standard GBA controller [in the bottom section, not the skinned one] so that you are presented with the nice and big B+A keys.

Next, open up Joypad connect on your PC and create a new profile configured like so:

[img]http://i.imgur.com/mq8FlZv.png[/img]


Your iPhone must be connected to your WiFi network, and should automatically show up in the GUI. With the App open on your iPhone, click the name of your device in the PC GUI and it will connect.

[img]http://i.imgur.com/MI8uT4n.png[/img]

Once connected, you can test it out by opening notepad and checking that the A+B buttons type Z and X. If you connect to the device several times you will notice it bugs out and will type xx or xxx for one keypress depending on how many times you have connected. To fix this simply restart the app and the pc application.

The app also includes several other nifty features such as using the accelerometer as a mouse [would be retarded for osu, but handy if you wish to set the A+B keys to mouse1 and mouse 2 and use it as a wireless mouse while you are sitting far away from the PC].

Happy touch streaming :)

9151.subject: RE: CS:S Timewarp
9151.message:
Timewarps for timer servers (bhop, trikz, kz) are impossible to make because the timer is server sided.
It's using GetEngineTime()/GetGameTime() from the time you start your timer until you finish it and subtract the end - start time to get your time.

Though, walking speed can be forced to 278.9 everytime by hooking CreateMove from client.dll + 0x21 and verifying the edited CUserCmd with pCommand->sidemove changed from 200 to -200 every tick.

9286.subject: RE: NOT WORKING !
9286.message:
I get that pretty often. Normally after a few tries I would be able to get it.
The mania replay extractor cannot extract every single song, but only most (Like 95%)
Try deleting ALL ur saved replays in your replay folder, then rewatch the replay. It may work.
If not, just restart your osu!
[hr]
If you are able to get the bot to hit notes but it always hits really bad notes (Like 100), the problem is with the Universal Offset. Try experimenting with the universal offset, mine is about -26ms, it's the best for my bot. Make sure your configurations are correct. Also, sometimes the bot may play the replay of another difficulty of the same song so make sure you empty your replay folder and re-watch the autoplay.

If all fails, then it means that your PC/laptop is really laggy... try another computer and get Kev to refresh your HWID

-The bot works perfectly fine for me, I too am an windows 7 user

9346.subject: Secret of getting good HR score! Or (DT)
9346.message: After using the relax program for around a year, I realized that hr is a pain in the neck to play with since it always gets me 97% at best even if I try my best. So couple of months ago, I was trying out some of the songs with hr and it hit me that perhaps the ar was the problem, so I changed my ar to 9 on enlighten and tried to do the song with hr. This, when naturally done, would get you ar 10, but when done with enlighten it keeps the ar at 9. When the ar became 9, I realized that the songs were much easier and my life became easier. So, I tried the same with dt songs, but unfortunately, dt songs actually scale up in ar. For example, ar 7 would become ar 9, ar 8 would become ar 9.67, and ar 9 would become ar 10.33. Therefore, it would be wise to stay around ar 7 or 8 for best performance. Have fun doing some hard maps out there guys :P

3. Just a suggestion for others: For FL "Try as hard as you can to reach the hitcircles with your cursor before the actually appear..." 

Perhaps setting AR lower with enlightened could help people here do that?

9996.subject: RE: osu!Enlighten, free for subscribers (FL/HD/HR hack.)
9996.message:
[quote='Daniel58' pid='9991' dateline='1384507559']
I got also no idea about how to use approach rate xD
[/quote]

Approach rate works like this:

If you set the AR to 8 (750 MS)

It will stay as AR 8 for everything apart from DT. 

So if you wanted to play AR 8 with DT enabled you would set your AR to 6 which would then be 8.33 with DT enabled.

You can find the AR conversion rates for DT here:

https://osu.ppy.sh/wiki/images/6/68/ARTable.png

It also shows you the MS delay for each AR so you can better fine tune what MS you are playing if you wanted.
